New Pro Quality 1200WS total 3 Strobe Light Kit (VE3400A). 
 
Vistarfoto spells quality, well made and beautiful equipment. The quality of VE PLUS durable series are extremely good though, consistent and affordable. They will provide you with all the power and lighting control that you will need to create professional-looking portraits and great still life tabletop photographs. 5-stop range. You can switch from full to proportional modeling with the press of a button. An audible flash-ready alarm lets you know when your VE PLUS flash light is fully charged and ready to go.

description:
I'm selling a brand new in a sealed box Apple iPad Air 2 WiFi + Cellular 64GB Space Gray.  Price is firm.  Cash only. 
 
Wi-Fi + Cellular Model 
If you're someplace where there is no Wi-Fi coverage, iPad with Wi-Fi + Cellular models let you stay connected to fast cellular data networks practically anywhere you go. So you can continue to browse the web, send and receive email, get directions, and more. 
 
Data plans in the U.S. 
With Wi-Fi + Cellular models, it's easy to choose a carrier and sign up for a cellular data plan that's right for you. You can get short- or long-term plans, or even low-cost share plans as part of an account you already have with a carrier. iPad Pro, iPad Air 2, and iPad mini 4 with Wi-Fi + Cellular come with Apple SIM preinstalled,* giving you the ability to conveniently choose and set up a cellular data plan right on your iPad. Participating carriers include AT&T, Sprint, and T-Mobile.** You can also purchase a fixed amount of cellular data for local use through pay-as-you-go providers like GigSky. Whichever plan and provider you choose, you'll get the connectivity you need for however long you need it.

title: New YAMAHA TF1 32 channel digital mixer
description:
TF1 is the easiest digital mixer to work on, even untrained church volunteers can mix on it after brief introduction! 36 inputs to mix, 20 onboard inputs, 16 onboard mic preamps (same recallable preamps as in QL/CL series), 16 outputs (freely assignable as mains, subgroups, monitor mixes, etc.).  
 
Mixer is NEW,  was bought it for a church project who decided to go with the larger Yamaha QL5  (a $12K desk) at the last moment, so this TF1 is for sale now. You can register it with Yamaha and get full warranty from day one. Firmware was upgraded to the latest v.3.01, the newest and cleanest TF1 money can buy. 
 
My price is more than reasonable: they are $2000-plus elsewhere, and there's hardly any used TF1's on the market now -- people just not selling them! Google "Yamaha TF1", you'd be surprised by for how much it sells even online! So your only option will be either to get a new one at full retail, or to get mine in the same new condition for at least $500 less. 
 
Channel structure is similar to well-known Yamaha 01v96 mixer: first input layer (1-16) is coming from onboard inputs (combo XLR-TRS jacks), second (17-32) is either USB or card inputs and outputs. Actually it has 20 onboard inputs, counting two pairs of stereo ins: you can use those for keyboards or drums submixes, or USB playback, leaving the rest for mono sources like mics and guitars. You can mix a typical 4-5 piece band on TF1 just fine, without any add-ons (most bands fit into 16 channels or less). 
 
You don't really need a snake with this mixer: leave it on stage, plug everything in and let musicians control their own monitor mixes right there, while sound guy can mix the FOH from anywhere in audience using iPad or laptop. 
 
TF1 allows individual per-channel input routing, not in blocks of 8 like X32/M32. Very convenient if you are using backing tracks from DAW during live performance: you can have 16-20 "live" inputs coming from stage combined with up to 34 DAW tracks (or any combination thereof).  If using Dante card input, you can have any Dante-compatible stage box feeding all 32 inputs from stage if desired (I doubt if it will be needed, realistically most 4-5 piece bands can fit into 16 channels or less). Dante is an audio communication protocol that allows up to 64 channels to be transmitted via single thin CAT5 Ethernet cable (pretty much a phone cord). Every respectable console manufacturer has Dante-compatible stage boxes, so you can use it with Soundcraft, MIDAS, Allen and Heath, Focusrite RedNet, they are all compatible. 
 
Nice feature is "Sub" bus. It's actually a third main bus (what others call "mono" or "center", you can use it that way), but the most important is that it has a LPF (low-pass filter), thus eliminating the need for crossover. Having separate "subwoofer" bus allows to route there only bass instruments (kick drum, bass guitar, bass synth), rather than filtering full mix, thus making low end tight, punchy and not muddy when using just a crossover. 
 
Mixer also works as a full-featured 34x34 USB audio interface (34 tracks can be simultaneously recorded and played back from DAW via single USB cable!). Allows you to have full multi-track recording of your performance (not just two-channel stereo), where every input will be recorded on a separate track and later finished in the studio.  
 
It's also a great recording console for home or project studios. Can be used with any DAW: Pro Tools, Logic, Cubase, Nuendo, Reaper, to name a few, with more flexibility and better preamps than in older "studio" desks such as 01v96, DM1000, 02r96, DM2000, etc. Even if you have no experience with DAWs, you can download free Waves Tracks or Reaper, capture your performance and just give files to someone who can finish them up in Pro Tools. 
 
What makes it special -- no surprise -- is the sound. Decades of research and development that made Yamaha digital consoles a standard in pro sound, all it shines in TF desks. And what makes it so easy to use are two things: a MULTI-TOUCH display (yes, you can scroll, pinch, zoom, tap, move virtual sliders just like on iPad. None of other digital mixers can do that, even Yamaha's own CL, QL and PM10! (those have touch screens but only single-touch, means you can select the parameter on the touch screen but can't turn, move, drag, pinch, zoom and do any of multi-touch gestures what TF desks can do). Second is Yamaha's patented "1-knob" approach to everything, lets you dial that perfect EQ, compressor, effect with one knob only, using Yamaha's preset algorithms (although you can have full control over all parameters such as gain, frequency, Q (bandwidth), threshold, attack, release, etc.) 
 
It's the easiest desk for monitor mixing: has no less than 20 (twenty!) monitor mixes, last six are stereo mixes for in-ears. Seriously, you can have 8 floor wedge monitors for choir plus six stereo in-ears for band musicians, all mixed independently. (The next desks in Yamaha lineup with that many monitor mixes are $20K-plus (even used) PM5D and CL series). All auxes can be stereo-linked, giving you 10 STEREO in-ear monitor mixes, more than plenty for a typical band or church service. (None of competitors can do that). All auxes work in sends-on-faders mode, and up to 10 iOS devices (iPhones or iPads) can be used as personal monitor mixers by musicians. In fact you are getting a full functionality of an Aviom personal monitor mixers for free and without 16-channel limitation of Aviom! 
 
Another feature that makes soundman's  life easy is on-screen RTA (Real-Time Analyzer). You see the whole audio spectrum right on the screen, overlaying EQ. Typical task of eliminating feedback with graphic EQ is a piece of cake: just look at the screen where the offending peak is and simply pull down the corresponding slider, right on screen too. You don't need to have a "golden ears" of a seasoned sound engineer or even know what that frequency it is: TF1 does it for you! All 8 wedge monitor outputs already have GEQs assigned to them, no need to route or mount anything. 
 
Here's a very detailed review from FOH magazine: 
 
"For years, Yamaha's digital mixers seem to set a standard by which other consoles are judged. There is no question that the PM1D, PM5D and M7CL are legendary consoles that defined their respective time periods and market segments. The CL and QL series consoles are no exception, and the PM10 Rivage is poised to be another staple of large-scale productions, much like its predecessor the PM1D. 
 
In the high-end of the digital console market, there are a plethora of exceptional consoles that are worthy of their price tags. The top of the line consoles are so feature-rich and sound so amazing that it's almost difficult to be wowed by them anymore. What has impressed me over the last few years has not been in the high end of the market, but at the lower end of the price spectrum. 
 
Enter the TF series of consoles. Based on Yamaha's TouchFlow technology, the TF series are truly one of-a-kind consoles that only Yamaha could deliver at this price point! Drawing on almost 30 years of digital console R&D and manufacturing experience, the TF series has something for everyone, from working musicians running their own sound, to the seasoned engineer needing an affordable, compact and feature-rich console. The TF line is clearly aimed at an underserved but growing market of users who require the flexibility and power of a digital console at an affordable price. But don't let its target market fool you, the TF series is packed with features often found on consoles costing four times as much. 
 
Under each input channel's scribble strip is a bright and colorful strip used to color-code channels into logical groupings. The scribble strip itself is also very large and high resolution. Once the TF fully booted for the first time, a tutorial appeared on the multi-touch screen that gave a rundown on some of the main features and console workflows. In typical fashion, I wanted to close the tutorial and dive right in, but I resisted the urge and powered through it, and it was actually very helpful. 
 
As I started to move my way around the surface, I really appreciated the layout and ergonomics, long one of Yamaha's strong suit. The multi-touch screen is responsive, and the GUI elements are just the right size for touch operation. While the screen is more than bright enough for indoor operation, it won't be bright enough outdoors, so break out the cardboard sunhood that you've fashioned for your other digital consoles. The buttons have a nice click that provides tactile feedback, and the knobs have an incremental click offering a feeling of precision control. The faders felt fairly smooth, although the fader caps themselves look and feel a bit cheap. For a console at this price point, I can't complain about the overall aesthetics. As I finished my cursory overview of the surface, I found a nice resting place for an iPad to run Yamaha's TF StageMix application. 
 
Working my way down the input channel strip, I found a layout familiar to any Yamaha user; the head amp, a 4-band EQ + high pass filter, a compressor, a gate and routing section. However, there were a few unique features that were jumping out at me. 
 
Entering the head amp section of the TF, I found a distinctive graphical level display that Yamaha calls "GainFinder." In an attempt to make setting gain structure more intuitive, there is a 5-segment horizontal meter, the center bar of which is a large green indicator denoting "ideal" gain structure. This is coupled with a more traditional vertical meter to the right, providing excellent visual feedback about the gain setting for each input. 
 
Second, the multi-touch screen is excellent for dealing with the input equalizers. The multi-touch screen was very responsive, but is admittedly not for everyone. Some engineers prefer the precision of a knob, so Yamaha has included a "touch and turn" knob below the lower right corner of the display, as well as four totally programmable user-defined knobs below the screen. What really caught my eye in the EQ section was a unique function called "1-knob." The EQ section can be operated in the traditional style, with complete control over the parameters of each filter, or you can switch to "1-knob." 
 
The 1-knob mode has two different settings; Intensity and Vocal. The Intensity mode is the default, which varies the gains of the filters you already have in place. For example, let's say on your kick drum you've got a 6 dB boost at 70 Hz, and a 6 dB cut at 300 Hz. When you engage 1-knob and start to apply it, it will boost your 60 Hz filter even more, and cut your 300 Hz filter further as well. It seems to only modify the gain of filters you already have engaged, and doesn't touch the frequency or Q, hence the name "Intensity." If you switch to the Vocal 1-knob mode, the first thing that happens is the EQ is flattened. As you dial up 1-knob in Vocal mode, it applies varying degrees of "typical" vocal equalization that will feel familiar to any experienced engineer. 
 
The input channels also include a wealth of presets available to help speed up the EQ workflow. These aren't just generic kick, snare, bass, guitar and vocal presets, but rather a well-thought-out set of presets that are specific to many instrument and microphone combinations. Yamaha developed these equalizer presets in conjunction with Shure, Sennheiser and Audio-Technica, as well as a host of respected sound engineers with decades of mixing experience. 
 
Speaking of presets, a full complement of onboard Yamaha effects are available, including an assortment of reverbs, mono/stereo delays, echo, flange, phaser and multiband compressors, derived from its larger siblings: CL, QL and the newest PM-10. 
 
All TF consoles have a generous eight mono and six stereo auxes, and the mono auxes can be linked as stereo pairs if necessary. What is really striking is the TF's emphasis on the "Sends on Fader" workflow for monitor mixing. As with most digital consoles, the TF provides several ways to do virtually everything, but console design promotes the use of "Sends on Faders" as the best method for mixing monitors. The right edge of the console has an entire panel of buttons devoted to this feature, so every mix is immediately available with a single button press. 
 
While sends on faders has been given a prominent place on the TF's surface, it doesn't quite tell the whole story. All TF models include the ability to have up to ten iOS devices controlling aux sends, using Yamaha's MonitorMix application. Couple that with up to three additional devices running TF StageMix or TF Editor, and even a large band can have independent control of their monitor mixes, reducing the demands placed on the engineer. 
 
Other Features: It's worth pointing out that I didn't touch the user manual once in this entire process, and I never felt I needed it because the console was so intuitive. It did take me a few minutes to find the eight DCA's, but once I discovered them, I found them easy to program, and they have an automatic "rollout" (or "DCA Spill") feature that spills channels assigned to the selected DCA across the surface. I could easily mix an entire show just from the DCA bank because of the rollout feature, but Yamaha has also included a custom user bank where you can include any combination of inputs, output masters or DCA's. 
 
I also discovered three small but ingenious buttons across the surface. First, a dedicated "Tap" button for tapping delay tempos. No, not a button that can be programmed as a tap tempo, but a button that actually says "Tap" on it, and flashes in sync with the current tempo. In the upper right of the console surface, I found two mute buttons labeled "Input" and "FX." Essentially preprogrammed mute groups, these buttons are dedicated to the two most common mute group applications; muting all inputs, and muting all effects. Brilliant! Finally, for those who need the more traditional Yamaha "User Defined Keys," those exist as well, directly to the right of the multi-touch display. 
 
A free download from Yamaha's website, TF Editor is a computer program that lets users use a PC to edit TF series console settings while away from the console in offline mode or -- in an online mode-- operate the console via the computer while it's connected to the console.  
 
All features are great, but the sound of the console is critical. Using some industry standard Shure and E-V mics, along with pre-recorded tracks, I quickly established gain structure on both microphones and my tracks using the GainFinder feature. Based on Yamaha's D-PRE mic amps, console's recallable (yet discrete-design) preamps were transparent sounding and true to both voice and the mics. Yamaha's documentation states the preamp was "painstakingly designed with a flat, wide frequency response that retains the tone and nuance of the original sound," and what I heard lives up to their description. Apparently it uses several discrete circuits, as you raise the gain you hear two distinct relay clicks (similar to old M7CL), when preamp switches from lower gain to higher gain circuit. 
 
The EQ's felt responsive as well, and I was able to discern even the slightest change, whereas on some consoles I feel like I have to cut 3 dB or more before hearing any appreciable change in tone. I also tested out the 1-Knob EQ in Vocal mode on the SM58 channel, and it performed just as I expected; a typical vocal response curve, with a dip in the low-mids to compensate for proximity effect, and a slight rise in the high-mids to add some presence. This gets you there (or close to it) fast, which can really come in handy in a live environment 
 
Conclusion: I found the TF series to be one of the most compelling digital consoles I've used in the last few years. The features contained in the TF desks would have cost upwards of $20,000 just five years ago, so the fact that these consoles sit in the sub-$5,000 market is truly astonishing. The console is the perfect blend of musician friendly ease-of-use and professional level control. It will be difficult for any other company to top what Yamaha has done with these consoles." 
 
Since you see this ad now, it means that mixer is STILL AVAILABLE. Emails asking that stupid question (or "Do you still have it?") will be treated as scam and ignored, you won't get a reply.  
 
Can be seen in San Mateo pretty much any day before 7.30pm., or in Sunnyvale after 8pm. I have all that's needed to test it (mics, speakers, etc), and it's under full factory warranty anyway.

I am a mechanical engineer and have put my expertise into carefully choosing part selection, order of assembly and integration of parts to make it a really solid vehicle. It handles well both on the road and on the track and has competed in many Autocross events. This car turns heads and I am constantly getting smiles and "thumbs up" wherever I go. This car is a looker with its super low stance and bright red paint. I have replaced and upgraded nearly the entire car in the 5 years I owned this. I spent careful attention to things that are unseen but make a huge difference in handling. The steering, brakes, power train, suspension all contribute to the joy this car is to drive. 
 
The car has participated in multiple Goodguys Autocross events and American Street Car Series weekends in CA. In 2013 we did the CA to Texas Hall Of Fame Road Tour ~3k miles round trip without issue. This car is RELIABLE. It has been a daily driver for several years.

title: 2001 Suzuki GSXR 1000
description:
I have a 2001 GSXR 1000 for sale. Its currently set up as a track bike, but it can easily be turned back into a street bike with very little hassle. The motor has been worked and puts out very linear power. It has a ported and polished 2003 head with a 2003 Fuel Injection rail and Power Commander III. I added Carillo Rods and Wiseco high compression pop-up pistons and many other go-fast internal parts. 
 
The forks have been worked as well and stripped of their stock internals. I replaced them with a full Race Tech adjustable set up which allows a custom set up for whoever rides it, with a complete range of compression and rebound damping settings.

title: 2006 Suzuki DRZ400SM
description:
Hello everyone, 
 
Up for sale is my 2006 Suzuki DRZ400SM. I recently bought a new bike and now my DRZ doesn't get ridden. I would rather have someone riding it and having fun, then have it sit in my garage. The bike is very clean and ready to go. Everything works, the bike is turn-key and needs nothing. If you're looking for a clean DRZ just to hop on and ride (unlike most that will need work) this would be a great bike. All of the registration and maintenance is up to date. Both tires were just recently replaced and have about 90% tread. I had a gold DID chain put on awhile back that is in very good condition, has at least another 10k miles on it. The brake pads also have plenty of life left in them (you can see the tire and brake pad meat on one of the pictures). Valves were adjusted in the last 2000 miles; so they won't need to be touched for another 15k miles at least. I do a full synthetic oil change every 1000 miles (even though the DRZ can go 3000 miles). The fork seals were done in the past year and won't need to be worried about for awhile. 
 
Upgrades: 
Full MRD exhaust, 3x3 mod, rejetted carb, pro taper evo bars, hel steel braided brake lines, IMS pro mx pegs, sumo front fender, and white spoke skins. I also have two sprockets; one smaller one for commuting and one larger for more bottom torque. My whole point when upgrading this bike was to do all the best power mods without screwing up with the DRZ's amazing reliability. The bike starts up perfectly every time. Bike has never quit on me or left me stranded. 
 
If interested please feel free to call/text/email me. I will not spend all day answering questions over text or email. I will only consider you serious if you call or come see the bike in person. Please don't waste either of our times. I'm in no rush to sell so no low-ballers and also not interested in trades. Thanks for looking!

I am un-enthusiastically putting my 2007 BMW 335i up for sale. First off, I must say that I am in no rush whatsoever to sell her. I am only putting her on the market because I now have a Corvette Z06 and am thinking of using my truck to commute. I am sure if you have come to this post, you know there must be something special about this car, since due to miles and the year, the KBB is much below what I am asking. This brings up my second point. If I am to sell this car, it will go to a very lucky buyer. When I purchased the car one year ago (December 2015), I went for the "great deal" on the 335i which I went out the door for $17,500 with 70K miles on the car (Included a couple packages still ongoing, listed below). Yes, I have done a lot of performance and cosmetic upgrades, but the main reason the value is so high to me, is that all of the common issues that happen between 60-120k miles have been serviced. I wanted this car to last a long time, and run very smoothly. Below you can see the modifications that have been done on the car. At the bottom I will put the cost of all parts I have invested in, and then the associated labor costs. Finally, there will be a cost total on top of what I paid for the car, and you can see the value that is here. If you want to find a "cheap 335i" then I suggest you look for one of the $9-12k ones, but let me tell you. . .YOU WILL NEED TO DO ALL OF THESE MAINTENANCE UPGRADES. I am selling this at even a lower cost than the parts added to the original price alone, so you would be getting a great deal (plus it looks and drives amazing). Feel free to throw out an offer and we can talk, but again I am in no rush at all. Thank you for visiting my post. 
 
Exhaust sound: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bS9Ub37yprI 
 
And to add to your comfort the car is smogged and registered until February 2018 and I am the second owner. The car comes with a ding shield contract and a yearly clay bar maintenance (when I purchased the car those were the two deals included. Essentially, anytime there is a dent they will take it out for free and anytime during the year you can bring it in for a clay bar and complete interior/exterior cleaning). The car has heated seats and a liner for ski's or snowboards through the middle back seat.  
 
The car has 430hp/560tq on the custom tune. It will easily pull on a E90 M3 (my friend has one so this has been confirmed). 
 
List of maintenance modifications: 
•	Spark plugs 
•	Valve cover gasket 
•	Coils 
•	Injectors 
•	Oil filter housing gasket 
•	HID Ballast 
•	Weather stripping 
•	High Pressure Fuel Pump has warranty until 120k miles 
•	Thermostat 
•	Water Pump 
 
List of performance parts installed since purchase: 
•	H&R springs 
•	Bilstein shocks 
•	COBB intake filter 
•	Synapse charge pipe 
•	Synapse BOV 
•	COBB downpipes (catted for easy smog) 
•	COBB full exhaust 
•	COBB Intercooler 
•	COBB Accessport 
•	Pro Tuning Freaks (PTF) custom 93 octane tune (other tunes including stock one available) 
•	Continental tires (not my first choice, but very good and tons of tread left) 
 
List of cosmetic parts installed since purchase: 
•	Black front grill 
•	Blacked out chrome trimmings 
•	Window tint 
•	Custom black and yellow vintage plate 
•	Black floormats 
•	Apex 18" rims 
•	Black and white BMW badges all around 
•	Carbon fiber BMW badges in Apex rims 
•	Front splitter, color matched 
•	Rear M3 spoiler, color matched 
•	Angel eye daytime white bulbs 
•	Side reflector eliminated 
 
Total Cost of Maintenance parts: $3,000 
Total Cost of Performance parts: $5,300 
Total Cost of Cosmetic parts: $2,500 
 
Total Cost of Maintenance install: $4,000 
Total Cost of Performance install: $3,000 
Total cost of Cosmetic install: $1,000 
 
Total cost of car December 2015: $17,500 
Total Cost of parts: $10,800 
Total Cost of install: $8,000 
 
Total Cost I have put in: $36,300 
My Asking price: $19,000 
Wear/Aging loss of value for one year: $5,000 
 
In my opinion you will be saving over $12,000, even taking into account wear over the last year. Additionally, you will not have to go through the pain of diagnosing, purchasing, and installation times where everything has already been done. I feel like this car is a child of mine since it has had so much work/customization done. Look forward to getting to know the next owner, it will not be easy to let her go. 
 
Please text, or call and leave a voicemail.  
 
Jeff

title: Selling used UNFILLED Kickboxing heavy bag and New focus mitts
description:

It has a D-ring on the bottom to secure to the floor or a sand bag for more stability see pictures. 
It's made of top quality 22oz heavy duty polyester coated vinyl material, this material is ideal when left outside in the elements for years as where leather tends to soak up moisture and break down more easily when left outside in the rain. 
 
 
Triple stitched with heavy duty 6-ply twisted polyester thread 
Metal D-Rings - High Quality- Welded Steel D-Rings. reinforcement inside where each D-Ring is attached 
 
You can fill it between 115 to 150 LBS and it measures 14" x 72" 
 
The top is not a zipper top it is a separate piece that attaches by string. 
 
When I bought it the bag didn't come with the string so I just used one I had laying around in the garage. But it works, it comes unfilled/empty.  
 
I am in the Bay Area a lot so I could meet you half way depending on the day and time if you're in the San Francisco/Oakland Berkeley/Napa, Solano County Area. I don't go to Sacramento for work so you would have to come to me if you're coming from the Vacaville/Sacramento area.  
You pick up I take cash only thank you.  
 
The size and shape of these punch mitts allows a trainer to work combinations with punches, Kicks, elbows and knees. This allows for better time management and better quality of instruction when working combos with students. 
These are $79.99 on Ring to Cage's website before shipping and handling and tax. 
 
They are made of leather and have an inner palm ball for comfort and extra padding to absorb shock for the trainer. It has a leather wrist strap with wide hook-and-loop closure which keeps the mitts firm and intact.  
I got drunk and went online shopping when I bought these but I already have these punch mitts so I don't need these that's why I'm just letting them go. 
My loss is your gain cash only you pick up, thank you.

title: Apple Cinema Display LED 27-Inch like Thunderbolt for Mac computers
description:
Perfect Screen no Scratches no Dead pixels. Its good to go! 
 
Just like the 24-Inch LED Cinema Display before it, the 27-Inch LED Cinema Display was designed as an "ideal companion" for MacBook, MacBook Pro and MacBook Air models as well as desktop Macs with a Mini DisplayPort (and it is not compatible with earlier Macs). The 27-Inch Apple LED Cinema Display features a 27-inch glossy LED-backlit TFT active-matrix LCD display with IPS technology and an optimum resolution of 2560x1440. It has a 178 degree horizontal and vertical viewing angle, a "typical" brightness of 375 cd/m2, contrast ratio of 1000:1, and a 12 ms response time. 
 
It includes three USB 2.0 ports and a convenient single cable with three connectors (Mini DisplayPort, MagSafe, and USB 2.0), a built-in iSight camera with a mic and a 2.1 speaker system.

title: 2014 Trek Session 88 DH Downhill MTB Bike Medium Red org.$6K+
description:
Bought new in 2015, 7-8 rides on it only local trails and few park trips. Just took to a LBS to get it checked out and tuned before this sale. Since the tune I rode it once and cleaned it, now its up for sale to find a new loving home. I am looking for 650b/27.5 bike at this point as I had this and a 29er and want to try 650b.  
 
Medium frame 
Comes with pedals 
 
MSRP NEW: $6379.99 
 
You find new lines on every run, or you make your own, on Trek's Session 88. This world-class downhill rig takes Trek's great aluminum frame and adds Fox's massive 40 fork up front with 203mm of some of the smoothest travel out there. In back, Fox is in control again with a sweet DHX coil delivering 210mm of madness with Trek's Full Floater and ABP suspension designs which isolates the suspension from braking input. Add Sun RinglÉ tubeless-ready wheels with a massive 12x157mm rear axle, SRAM X9/X0 shifting and the 88's DH-specific geometry and you realize that the view from the top step of the podium is as sweet as they say. 
 
reviews: 
 
 ive been riding my 2010 session88 for just over 2 monthes, and it rails everything.... i have built it from the frame up, and i think its worked out at £3000 (baring in mind ive had a few things super cheep) but it is pinned over everything. i took it to a track called foel gasnach yesterday and its rooty, ruted out, rocky, tight, super tech, super steep and it felt like the bike was asking for more and i was absolutely pinning it on some sections .... i had a 2004 V10 before this and the session88 feels alot smootherthan the V10 but still doesnt loose that snappyness when accelerating, and another big plus is that on flowy switchbacksyou litterally let the bike do the work... basicly you dont need to brake, just throw it into the corners and it does the job!  
 
bottom line......... GET ONE. frame or whole bike. either way with 26" wheels and 203mm forks you cant go wrong! 
 
I just picked up the 2010 Session with the help of the guys at Trek Bikes. The bike is honestly the best bike I have ridden, super easy to pedal and very plush going down the hill. It takes anything you can throw at it with the 203mm travel. Very responsive with the stock parts, I have yet to change anything on it for the month I have had it. Frame is super sturdy and light for a stock DH bike. I definetly recommend it to any DH racer or anyone that wants a "Grade A" bike, you wont regret it! 
 
 the best bike i ever possessed, after a few modifications at the front (new low stem, removing the spacers, wider bar) it works perfect, super light, super agile, well-balanced in the air and on the ground, beautiful frame and the suspension concept is unexampled 
 
The first thing you notice os the sheer beauty of the thing, after you get over that you feel the weight and it truly is unbeleivable.Secondly on the trail it goes round corners like no other Due to the low BB height and the pedaling efficency is on another level. Finally all the components work to the heighest level and compliment the bike nicely, i bought one and never looked back 
 
 I love my Session, it pedals better than any 8" bike I've ever ridden, suspension feels stable but plush, and the top shelf components make this bike great right out of the box. I changed the wheel set, installed a direct mount stem from Sunline, and slapped on my Minions, tubeless of course. I may still change the seatpost and saddle, but otherwise, Trek put out a bike that is just as good as anything I could have built from the frame up. Oh, the big earl pedals are like bricks, I'd recommend a lighter set with a bit lower profile. I'm doing Specialized Lo Pro Mags, in gold. 
 
 perfectly tuned suspension. 
 
incredibly light frame.  
 
stiffer than anyone else. 
 
flickable, yet stable at speed. 
 
in a few words -- it doesn't get any better than this!!

description:
Irrigation o'clock hunters remote control commercial, residential  
$140.00 
Local pickup: 
Paypal: 
Shipping: 
 
Hunter Irrigation Sprinkler Commercial Remote Control Kit, New, ICR-Kit  
 
New, in very good working condition. Kit is complete except for the 4 AA batteries. It was bought some time ago, but never used. Batteries were removed due to age.  
 
For shopping centers, industrial complexes, college campuses, condominiums, and other expansive sites. If a remote control is going to work it needs the power to cover long-range distances. The ICR has a signal strong enough to go through obstructions such as buildings, walls, or trees and communicate with a controller for a half mile or more. When nothing is in its path, the ICR can function up to two miles from the controller. The ICR is a single unit that can be carried from job to job and used to remotely access dozens of diﬀerent irrigation systems (including any Hunter controller that operates with a SmartPort system). That eliminates going back and forth to the controller to start or stop a cycle during maintenance or installation. The task of winterizing a system becomes a one-person job instead of two.  
 
Features:  
· Over ½ mile typical range. Control sprinklers, valves, and pumps without going directly to the controller.  
· Compatible with all Hunter controllers. Designed to work with all Hunter ICC, Pro-C and SRC controllers through a SmartPort connection.  
· Large LCD display, push button operation. User-friendly features make the remote simple to use.  
· Variable remote activated station run times. Allows a one-time change in station run time duration without affecting the regular program.  
· Operates on 4 AA batteries for up to a year. Automatic shutoff extends battery life when not in use.  
· 128 different programmable security codes. Allows multiple ICR receivers to be used in the same area.  
· Rugged plastic carrying case. Foam lined case protects ICR from rough handling.  
 
Model ICR-KIT -- Complete Kit: transmitter, receiver, and wiring harness, 4 AA alkaline batteries (not included), and plastic carrying case  
· ICR-TR -- Hand held transmitter  
· ICR-R -- Receiver unit  
· ICR-Case - storage case  
· Smartport port adapter and wiring harness  
· 28 page Owner's User/Installation Manual (English, Spanish)  
 
Dimensions  
• Transmitter (w/o antenna): 6½" H x 3¼" W x 1¼" D (16.5 cm H x 8.3 cm W x 3.2 cm D)  
• Receiver (w/o antenna): 6¼" H x 3" W x 1¼" D (15.9 cm H x 7.6 cm W x 3.2 cm D)  
 
Speciﬁcations and Features  
• Address range: 0 to 127  
• Maximum stations supported: 48  
• Run times: Eight settings from 1-30 minutes  
• Range: Up to ½ mile obstructed, up to 2 mile line of sight  
• Temperature: 0-150˚ F  
• Humidity: Up to 100%  
• Transmitter: 4 AA alkaline batteries (not included)  
• Receiver: 24VAC, 0.05 Amps from controller through a SmartPort connector  
• System operating frequency: 27 MHz band  
• Install SmartPort up to 50' from controller (use SRR-SCWH shielded cable wiring harness)  
• No FCC license required  
• Rugged plastic carrying case included

title: Roland VS 2400 CD + Roland SI-24 Studio Interface Package
description:
Here we have a very nice and in excellent condition Roland VS 2400 CD, easy to use and ready to record solo or the whole band! As you most likely know the VS 2400 CD is a self-contained in-the-box unit that does it all, no computer needed. The features are many and this Roland is rated very high, just Google the reviews. BTW, this is up on eBay as well but if it's still up on Craigslist, it's still for sale. 
 
See http://www.emusician.com/gear/1332/roland-vs-2400cd---the-no-hassle-pro-studio/33329 and https://www.roland.com/us/products/vs-2400cd/ 
 
Like the Korg and Tascam units out there, the VS 2400 CD has everything you need (but a microphone and a set of headphones) to make your high quality 24-track recordings and then burn it down to a CD. But, unlike many of those other units when you plug in a VGA life gets easier! Not only that, it's portable! Use the included well-built anvil case, put it in the car and record a high quality mix of next weekends gig or your buddies' band at their place, leave the computers, interfaces and chords at home! This far exceeds that good old Zoom you have been doing it on and there's no need for a laptop, all the interface equipment and cables, if you go that way now. You can also put the recording in an exportable file and mail it along to the band mates when mixed! Remember, these units have all kinds of in and out connections, check all the documentation on line. 
 
Here's what is included with this package.  
 
A. First, along with this VS 2400 CD is an included and in very good condition Roland SI-24 Studio Interface, the included (and pricey....) RBUS Cable to connect both machines, giving you eight more XLR inputs for a total of 16! In addition to the eight studio-quality mic preamps, the SI-24 has the motorized faders and a joystick for doing surround panning. The Roland SI-24 also can be used as a "surface control" for certain versions of Pro Tools, Cuebase and Lodic PRO. 
 
B. Second, this package includes a very nice LCD 22" monitor. Looks great and has the picture at a size fitted well for the eyes at near field range. And, I'll include the small little Dell Monitor that came with the package if you want it. I don't think there's anyway to run two monitors but let me know. 
 
C. Third, Lots of documentation and instructional media to get up on day one (one set for you, one for a partner). Two complete sets of DVD and a set of VHS. Two complete Roland VS 2400 CD manuals One complete manual for the Roland SI-24 Studio Interface. There lots of manuals and information on-line for the looking. 
 
D. Fourth, this package includes the mouse and keyboard and of course all the power cables as well. 
 
F. Also, this VS 2400 CD has an upgraded hard drive, lots of room, but I'll include the smaller original. 
 
Will deliver to the Bay. Contact for details!

title: Complete vandal proof outdoor megapixel network PTZ security camera
description:
I'm selling a complete outdoor vandal proof HDTV 1080P 300x PTZ network security system: Tyco American Dynamics Illustra 625, Sony Outdoor vandal proof UNIORS7T1, wall mount, power adapter, software.  This is the same as the Tyco American Dynamics ADCi625-P122 excep this system is vandal proof.  The whole system is complete assembled and tested.  It is ready to go and you should be able to just mount it up and start monitoring your property without spending hours looking for parts, assemble the system or configuring things.  I will provide a demo at the time of purchase so you can see how easy it is to hook the camera up and use it as well as seeing the camera in action.  I will include the link to the video of the camera that I recorded during my testing (see link below).   
 
The American Dynamic Illustra 625 is a US made camera and it's extremely powerful.  The quality of this camera comparable to those top system out there such as Axis q6035-E or Pelco S5220-EG0; except you pay a fraction of the price.  If you are serious about your business and property and looking for an exception security system, read further down as I will try to describe the camera's features as best as I can so you can make an informed decision. 
 
- Full HDTV 1080P 2MP video resolution with 30x optical zoom:  You no long have to worry about blurry images of a suspicious person 20,30ft away or a vehicle parked a block away.   No matter how small or big your property is, this camera will cover every spot with crystal clear images.  Seeing is believing so I'm providing the actual video of the camera that I recorded during my testing: 
 
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PiVM4QnwlzI 
 
The video is a recorded of a browser session.  Because this camera is network camera, you can connect to it using any web browser.  You can then easily view, control and configure the camera from there.  In the video, the jeep is couple hundred feet away and check out the crystal clear image of the license plate when I zoom in.  The trail across the canal is more than 200 yards and I can see people walking and running from the trail.  The low bridge is .5 mile away and the high bridge is 3/4 mile from the camera.  I purposely zoom in and out so you can compare between the actual distances.  You have to see the video for yourself to see how powerful this camera is.  Why spend the same more for some static cameras or some china made cameras that can't provide your the the crystal clear video that this camera can. 
 
- High speed continuous 360° pan and 210° tilt with real time continuous auto focus:  You will be able to cover every non-obstructed area with this camera since it has an endless 360° pan and 210°.  It has a super fast 510° per second movement so you can quickly move to a location.  It will autofocus on objects as you move and zoom so you don't have to adjust anything.  All you have to do is move the camera and zoom in/out of objects and the camera will do the rest of adjusting focus and Iris (for lighting).  In the video, I never had to touch any manual focus or Iris as the camera did everything for me. 
 
- Supports multiple presets, pattern and sequential patrol, and privacy zones:  This camera can be programmed to remember different positions with different zoom levels.  You can quickly move the camera to those presets with a press of a button.  This eliminates the need to manual pan or tilt the camera to the locations that you want to monitor.  You can camera programmed to zoom down the parking lot entrance a few hundred feet away as one preset and another preset to point the camera to the warehouse entrance.  You can then quickly move the camera between these presets within a second or so with a press of a button.  This camera has 96 presets available so you can very much cover all areas on your premise.  
 
    You can also set the camera to automatically patrol based on a recorded pattern, between the presets, or just scanning.  For areas that you don't want to monitor or displayed, you can set them as privacy zones so the camera will exclude those areas. 
 
- Wide Dynamic Range and True day/night feature for low light support:  This camera support WDR that provide auto adjustments of areas with different lighting condition to ensure that all objects appear clearly.  For example, in half shaded area, this camera can adjust the lighting of the sunny area and the shaded area so that objects don't get to washed out in the sun or to dark in the shade.  This camera is also equipped with ICR (Infrared Cut Filter) which changes the camera from color to black and white mode automatically when lighting condition becomes low.  In ICR mode, the camera can absorb more light so the images can be seen more clearly and it becomes sensitive to Infrared light which allows it to be used with external Infrared illuminators in complete darkness environment (0lux).  This camera can support as low as 0.04lux in black and white mode.   
 
- Support MicroSD card for local storage area:  This camera does not requirement external devices such as DVR/NVR to be able to record video from the camera.  The micro SD card will provide direct storage on the camera for direct recording, FTP, or emailing.  A 32Gb microSD is included with this system and will be fully inserted and ready to be used. 
 
- Fully ONVIF 2.0 compliant:  ONVIF standard provides cross application compatibility which means that you can use any application  supporting ONVIF to connect to any ONVIF compliant camera to view, record, and control the camera.  So if you have existing ONVIF 2.0 NVR application or devices, you can easily connect them to this camera to view and record video. 
 
- Fully outdoor support:  The housing UNIONS7C1 is equipped with thermostat controlled heater/blower to provide support for outdoor weather environment.  The outdoor housing can support temperature -20°F (-29°C) to 122°F (50°C).   
  
There are too many features to list them all.  You can see more information from the product page: 
 
http://www.americandynamics.net/Products/illustra-625-PTZ-camera.aspx 
 
For features and specs:  http://www.americandynamics.net/Resources/GetDoc.aspx?p=1&id=39546 
 
For camera configuration and user guide:  http://www.americandynamics.net/Resources/GetDoc.aspx?p=1&id=39783 
 
For Sony housing: http://pro.sony.com/bbsc/ssr/cat-securitycameras/cat-securitycameraaccessories/product-UNIORS7T1/ 
 
Local pickup and cash only

title: 2011 Dinan S1 BMW M3 Convertible (w/ extras)
description:
My family has grown and with the addition of a new family car, I have more cars than I have room for and unfortunately it is time to let go of my beloved 2011.75 BMW M3 Convertible.  This car is immaculate, you will not find a cleaner or better cared for M3 around.  This car is fully loaded with every option available from BMW.  The sticker price was almost $90k.  I won't bore you with a page long list, but the bottom line is that if BMW offered it, this car has it.  This car has always been garaged and is professionally detailed twice a year.  No accidents or body work and never tracked. 
 
This car has 27k miles on it and was used as my commuter from Pleasanton to Palo Alto.  It has been a joy to drive.  I distinctly remember waking up before my alarm in anticipation of my drive to work.  It has never been tracked.  All services have been performed and the car needs nothing.  Tires (Bridgestone RE-71Rs) have ~90% tread and registration is paid and current.  Just take the keys and enjoy. 
 
The Basics... 
4.0l V8 (One of the best sounding engines of all time) 
7 Speed DCT Transmission 
Top Level Stereo (Individual I Believe) 
2011.75 (Means it has all the upgrades of the 2012 but is technically a 2011) 
Retractable hardtop convertible 
 
On to the upgrades..... 
 
The major upgrade is the Dinan S1 kit which was installed by Dinan at a cost of just over $8,500.  The S1 package includes the Dinan Exhaust, Dinan Intake, Engine software upgrade, Dinan Stage 1 Suspension w/ supplemental ride quality and handling kit, Dinan strut tower bars, and Dinan Pedals  In addition to the S1 package the car has Dinan's DCT software upgrade as well. (I did end up removing the intake as Dinan never got it CARB approved). 
 
The car also has a full custom clear bra on all the front panels.  This is not a pre-cut kit, but a custom wrap by Auto Pro Films.  Cost was $1,500 for the wrap. 
 
Windows were tinted by Rocky Mountain Window Tint professionally at a cost of ~$500. 
 
I also decided to replace the rod bearings.  If you have not researched these cars, you may ask why with such low mileage.  If you have researched these cars, you will know that you can't spend more than 5 minutes on the M3 forum without becoming paranoid that your rod bearings might fail at any minute.  The rod bearings were replace with OEM WPC treated bearings by Performance Technic in Dublin.  If you know BMWs then you know Performance Technic.  Cost was about $2,200 for the bearings. 
 
Although this car is fully loaded, I was surprised to find there was never and option for a backup camera.  I added an aftermarket camera that was installed by Alekshop.  Cost was ~$350 installed. 
 
Alekshop also installed the M-performance style carbon rear spoiler.  Cost was ~$500. 
 
The stock wheels were also coated gloss black inside which hides brake dust very well and looks great. 
 
Over $14k total in upgrades and as you can see, I have only used the best shops in the bay area for any work performed on this car. 
 
Feel free to email with any questions.

title: Telepresence Robot Video Conferencing (New Condition)
description:
Please Call: 
  
 
 
 
Brand New Condition 
 
 
Lateral Stability Control 
Lateral Stability Control is a shock absorption mechanism built in the base to maintain lateral stability while traversing common obstacles in an office or classroom setting, such as cords, bumps, or a change in threshold. 
 
Power Drive 
Power Drive enables the robot to go up to 80% faster than normal driving speed, when the driver needs to go a long distance. Simply hold down the Shift key on your keyboard while driving with the arrow keys. 
 
 
Camera Kit 
Camera Kit includes a 150 degree wide-angle lens that increases the field of view by 70% on both the left and right sides! It's a 5 megapixel camera, so you can take much higher resolution photos to see the details. 
 
Camera Kit enables the Always-on Floor View for increased spatial awareness and no need to take time switching between camera views. Adaptive HD is a new technique that we've developed to favor smooth video when moving and higher resolution (up to HD!) when you're still. 
 
Camera Kit is Backwards Compatible! 
 
We always strive to reward our early, loyal customers. We were able to develop the Camera Kit accessory to be backwards compatible with first generation Double units, so you can get the wide field of view, Always-on Floor View, and Adaptive HD for just $249. Camera Kit plugs into the iPad's Lightning connector. We highly recommend using an iPad Air 2 or iPad Pro (9.7"), although an iPad Air or iPad 4 will also work, but with only some features and at lower resolution.

title: Semi-Professional Haynes Amadeus Flute
description:
To all of my Flute Friends and Instructors,  
 
I am selling my Amadeus 900 Flute. This is a semi-professional Flute made by Haynes' Beijing workshop paired with a hand cut Haynes Headjoint. Sterling Silver Tube (Headjoint, Body, and Foot), Silver-Plated Mechanism, B-Foot with Gizmo, Offset-G Key, C Sharp Trill Key, .16 body, Straubinger Pads, and comes with three crowns -- the original heavy silver crown, a cocuswood crown, and grenadilla Trevor James Crown. The Flute was purchased in the Summer of 2010 for Conservatory playing and has been my main instrument up until now. Plating on the mechanism is in excellent condition except on the D-sharp key where there is a little bit of wear from normal use.  
 
The instrument has been used in several recordings and solo playing. It has been used in many orchestra concerts and has a beautiful sound -- warm and immediate overtones. The cut of the head joint provides a quick response, even flexibility, and ability to shift between dynamic ranges is a breeze. It was recently serviced by Steve Deutsch in Berkeley. He gave it a full service including pad replacement, key level, and adjustment, ensured the tube is round and all joints fit perfectly, and a cleaning.  
 
I am letting this instrument go because I have purchased a newer instrument to replace this one. It comes with the original french style case which has a tiny bit of wear on the right-hand corner, and the original leather carrying bag. Also included are a wooden cleaning cloth and Flute Pro Shop polishing clothing. You can view recordings of this flute on my website: artietrodriguez.wix.com/psychomuze 
 
Asking $2500 or best offer.  
 
Serious buyers only. If you would like a time to set up a viewing and try the instrument out, please let me know. NO INTERNATIONAL BUYERS.  
 
If you have any questions, feel free to contact me.

title: Custom Liquid Cooled Gaming Computer - 3930k, GTX Titan, 2x 512GB SSD
description:
This custom liquid cooled computer was originally built specifically for editing, hence the 64GB of RAM, but is an amazing gaming rig. It is the quietest computer I've ever built and most people don't even know it is on besides the glowing fans. I wanted to make a computer that could run quietly and efficiently at any load. Even though it may be a few years old it still is cray fast and has a lot of potential for overclocking, although it was never attempted as I didn't have a need. It was hooked up to a 4k monitor and I occasionally played GTA V at well over 60 fps at near maxed out settings. I am letting this creation of mine go because space became and issue and being almost 3 feet tall and 2 1/2 feet long it takes up quite a bit of space. I wish I could keep what I've created but I sadly just need something smaller. The case is not in perfect condition, although it looks pretty good for being a 3 year old case (I bought the case a while before building the computer). Changes have been made overtime so there are some holes inside the case where old tubing was run and what not (as show in the pictures). It is all hard line acrylic tubing inside that I bent slowly with much trial and error. All of the visible fittings are matched, but as you can see in the photos, some of the internal non visible ones are not. There is currently 2 Samsung 512GB 840 Pro SSD's in RAID 0. I will load what ever OS you want onto the computer (it is currently running ubuntu server as I was having some fun with it a while back) and I can attempt to reload OS X onto it for a hacktintosh. This is something I did when I first built the computer and ran it this way for a month or so before switching to Windows 7.  
 
Specs: 
 
CPU: Intel 3930k 
Motherboard: Asus Rampage IV Extreme 
GPU: Asus GTX Titan SC (Super Clocked) 
RAM: 64GB G.Skill Sniper 1600mhz 
SSD's: 2x Samsung 512GB 840 Pro RAID 0

title: 2007 GSXR 1000 Track bike
cityName: hercules, pinole, san pablo, el sob
description:
I am selling my 07 GSXR 1000, I HATE to let it go but it's necessary for a couple of reasons... mostly involving my wife. 
 
This is a turnkey, ready to fly race/track bike with thousands of dollars worth of aftermarket parts and professional servicing. The bike has a 07 frame with rebuilt motor, now approximately 4000K. It is completely tech-ready according to AFM and WERA rulebooks. All you need to provide is some leathers and helmet to pilot this Production/Superbike/Legacy. In the 2017 AFM season, this bike will become eligible to run in the Legacy Heavyweight class, making it a very fast contender! Also included is:  
Extra set of painted fairings with a matching spare gas tank, Woodcraft rear sets (spare), front and rear stands, wheel chock and other miscellaneous parts. Here is a list of most of the aftermarket parts that are on the bike now: 
 
Driven:  
axle block sliders, clip-ons, oil cap, front and rear sprocket with 520 chain, D-Axis rear sets, brake lever guard.  
 
Woodcraft:  
rear brake return spring, all engine covers (red aluminum sliders), brake fluid reservoir mount.  
 
Bazzaz: Z-Fi TC (fuel mapping and traction control), TC light (traction control indicator), Z-AFM (self-mapper with O2 sensor), handlebar switch and dial for 2 fuel map settings and traction control settings. 
 
GPR4 steering dampener.  
ASV brake and clutch levers.

The Bazzaz fuel map switch is set-up for 50/50 (91 and 100 octane mix) and u4 race fuel, this can be changed to your preference. The Bazzaz has been tuned and configured for optimal acceleration throughout the power band and the traction control is set-up for race conditions, although it is completely adjustable.  
 
This bike has been issued a Nonrepairable Vehicle Certificate from the CA DMV. title: Pioneer DDJ-T1 Controller for DJing
description:
The Pioneer DDJ-T1 controller is the perfect integration of Traktor DJ software and Pioneer operability. The DDJ-T1 offers the same operability and layout as Pioneer's pro-DJ equipment, while enabling DJs to play music files from the computer via dedicated Traktor DDJ-T1 edition software. 
 
The controller is in perfect condition. It has hardly been used at home, and has been taken out to one gig only. It sells for $700 new (that's how much I paid for it), but I'm letting it go for $400. A steal. 
 
The DDJ-T1 easily connects with a user's laptop via USB for quick "plug-and-play" capability. For further convenience, the controller also comes with a computer dock that allows a laptop's keyboard to slip directly under the controller, bringing the monitor closer to the DJ, providing fast visuals of song information while mixing. The device adopts Pioneer's "P-LOCK Fader Cap," designed to prevent the fader caps from slipping. 
 
Key Features Include: 
 
* Plug-and-Play USB Connectivity -- All buttons and knobs have been pre-assigned, so users can quickly connect the controller to their laptops by USB cable and start their performances without having to adjust any complicated settings. Additionally, the DDJ-T1 can be powered through the laptop's USB port. 
 
* Specially Designed User Interface -- The controller layout and TRAKTOR software interface are identical, ensuring ease-of-use and precise control. The DDJ-T1 is modeled after the proven design of the professional Pioneer DJ player and mixer and integrates 115mm jog dials, accurate search functionality to quickly find playback points, a load button for song data and a master synch button for beat matching across four channels. 
 
* Highest-Quality Sound -- The controller is optimized for the TRAKTOR DJ software and incorporates technology from Pioneer's professional line of DJ equipment to ensure the highest quality sound output that DJs have come to expect from Pioneer products. 
 
Additional Features include: 
1. Proprietary lock mechanism called the P-LOCK Fader Cap designed to prevent fader caps from slipping. 
2. Premiere built-in sound card 
 
For detailed specifications, visit  
http://www.pioneerelectronics.com/PUSA/DJ/Controllers/DDJ-T1#overview 
 
Traktor software is not included.

title: Vintage 1960s Teisco electric guitar
description:
Sadly parting with my beloved Teisco single pickup electric guitar. I sold my amp a few months back, so hanging onto this seems a little silly and it was starting to look more like dollar signs sitting in a case.  
 
Purchased early in 2014 at DiPinto Guitars in Philadelphia, this guitar has most certainly had a long and loving life in the line of duty. Can't speak on its history before owning it myself, but it had clearly been well-used and well-loved. 
 
This lil guy's got one single pickup with a volume and tone nob, super simple. I really love the sound of this thing, its got a really great range even with the one tone control. I've never been into guitar gear with a million knobs and buttons so this is ideal if thats your approach too. With a pretty thin neck and body, you can really bend and shake the whole instrument if you wanna get weird and wobbly. Of course, this means it won't hold its tune if you go nuts but thats sort of obvious. Thats probably the only downside to this guitar, given its age it needs pretty consistent tuning-peg tweaking to keep it in tune. Could certainly use a setting-up by a pro.  
 
Cosmetic wear all around (I mean, its 50 years old, I'm just glad it still works). Missing one of the screws from the pick-guard but thats easily replaceable if you care (I obviously didn't, it still plays ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ ). Couple stickers too, if you want I can peel those off before a sale.  
 
SO, if you're looking for a guitar with a story and a history, just want a unique instrument (still have never seen this exact model #rare), or wanna look like Mac Demarco or make a Mac Demarco ripoff band and indulge in reverby weed-grunge and look super hip doing it then THIS IS YOUR WEAPON.  
 
Asking $200 cash 
 
I've got a hard case that the guitar fits in as well. The case isn't made for the Teisco, but the guitar is fairly small so it fits. I would say it'll likely fit in most cases with a bit of room to spare. $200 firm with the case included. If you just take the guitar, we can maybe negotiate on price.

title: 2004 Specialized M4 Stumpjumper, XTR, UPGRADED 18" (was $5500 new)
description:
You're looking at my belived 20th Anniversary Special-Edition 2004 Specialized Stumpjumper FSR Pro mountain bike. It has a 18" frame (I am 5'7"). This bicycle has all Shimano XTR components and hydraulic disc brakes. This is a full suspension mountainbike. I purchased this mountainbike back in 2004. It has upgraded components. Everything you see was top of the line in 2004 (other than the frame itself: S-Works) such as Mavic rims, XTR everything, S-Works handle bar, Thomson Elite stem, Fox Forx shocks, Chris King headset, and more. As-is with the components shown, it cost $5500 back then.  
The bicycle is in excellent condition (has some minor scuffs, scratches as expected from a bicycle this age). I've put less than 1000 miles on this bike in it's lifetime, and I've done roughly 20 tune-ups (average 2 a year). I've replaced the chain a few times, tires, and other parts. I am always being told that the bicycle is in amazing condition. It is ultra-light for a mountainbike and handles extremely well. You won't find anything better for this price. The technology for mountain bikes has not changed that much in the last decade. Great for single track, off-road, or as a daily cruiser. Nothing but premium components only. 
 
The only reason why I am selling this bicycle is due to on-going/chronic knee problems. I can longer ride pain-free. I've put less than 10 miles on it in the last 1 1/2 years. It's tine to let it go so someone else can enjoy it. 
 
Please note: the front shock is not locking out properly anymore. It would need to be fixed by a shop (sent in to the manufacturer) if you want it to work or a replacement fork can be purchased online (I started looking on eBay, but due to my knee issues, I never purchased one). 
 
The bicycle is located in the Marina near Ft. Mason. 
 
$1100 OBO.

title: DJI Phantom Drone Quadcopter 1.1.1 with extras!  Better than v2
description:
Hello 
 
Selling my complete ready to go Dji phantom v 1.1.1 like new with box, charger, transmitter, prop guards, manual, extra battery, extra new oem propellers, installed Walkera brushless gimball----ready to fly! Gopro not included. 
 
These were special editions which have the upgraded NAZA v2 board for better GPS reliability, the gimbal adjustment lever on the back of the controller, screw off propellers for better transport and swap out, and an easy to access sync button for syncing a new transmitter if needed (before u would have to take the shell apart)   
 
In addition to those featutures I have installed the summitlink snap on/off prop guards (along with drilled access holes in the snap on mounts for easier future motor access), a new in bag set of oem Dji propellers, an extra DJI battery without that many cycles, a cleanly installed brushless Walkera G-2D gimbal which i installed longer screws so yes it will fit will your older Go pro hero 2 wide body or hero 3, etc.  you can record hd video and audio along with top down and straight ahead views, btw do not use the gopro's wifi.  (gopro not included). No jelly effect on the video, beautiful stable recordings.  New in box Balance charger BC20-4 never used for lipo or LiFe, 1s,2s,3s, or 4s with US and international AC power plugs, the fixed gopro mount is also included, along with the standard shorter landing legs if you decide to remove the gimbal.   
 
The latest firmware is installed and everything works flawlessly and is ready to fly!  Software linking to pc works great where you can dial in gimbal throws, altitude limits, and program the transmitter switches if you want.  Current right switch setup is GPS mode, attitude mode, and return to home.  Also you are able to enable flight characteristics with the left transmitter top switch to suit beginners regardless of nose direction and of course if the transmitter is turned off it will fail safe return to home. 
 
Never crashed and in really excellent condition, never had any problems with this drone!  If this is your first drone, I can walk you through it. 
 
Located in Campbell

title: Rescued JBL 128H Woofer NEW Surround L112 L150 L150A 4411 120Ti 4412
description:
Rescued JBL 128H Woofer & Refurbished with New Foam Surround plus 24-Hour Burn-In 
 
One Rescued JBL 128H with Original Cone & Voice Coil with New Spider, Dust Cap plus Fresh Foam Surround 
 
Tested all the way to Xmax with a 30Hz signal to verify the voice coil does not rub - Ready to Go! 
 
The new foam surround was installed on the REAR of the cone (NOT the face) and 4 used silver mounting screws which will be included! 
 
And look......Pro silver input terminals posts, not the early consumer version! 
 
Low Frequency Transducer: Model 128H, felted paper cone laminated with White Aquaplas, cast aluminum frame, nominal 12 inch diameter, 3 inch copper voice coil, 10 lbs. magnet. 
 
Refurbished by VSN on eBay 
Removed: Cone Assy / Rotten Foam Surround / Internal Disk 
Cleaned: Basket, Silver Rim, Face Gaskets & Cone 
Inspected: Input Terminals 
Installed: New Foam Surround / Port Mesh Screen / Spider & Aligned 
Confirmed with Sound: Clear and Smooth 
24 Hour Burn-In with 50% Xmax @ 30Hz signal 
 
This white Aquaplas cone woofer used primarily in the L112, L150, L150A, L150A-B or 4411 
 
As sounds exactly like the later black Aquaplas cone woofer so it can be used as a replacement in the 120Ti, 4412 & 4412A monitor, yet most JBL fans will avoid the color change simply to keep their systems original. 
 
The 128H or the 128H-1 are 100% acoustically identical, with the only visible difference is being the cone color. 
 
In addition to getting a new foam surround, the internal foam disk used as a screen over the magnet port has been removed and replaced with a non-rotting fine mesh screen.

title: 2016 Scott Genius 710 Plus - Year End Sale - Size Small in Stock
description:
The 2016 Genius 710 Plus from Scott represents the next big thing to hit the dirt. Designed around a new wider hub and bottom-bracket profile, called Boost, and clearance for 3 inch wide tires on 27.5 inch rims the Genius 710 Plus brings an entirely new level of traction and control to the trail. Add the proven full-suspension design of the Scott Genius to this bigger platform and the result is a bike that devours big roots or small boulders and sticks to slippery singletrack without slowing down. SRAM GX1 components equip this plus-sized bike with a 11 speed drivetrain and the additional clearance to truly go anywhere. The stopping duties are aptly handled by a set of Shimano hydraulic disc brakes with 180mm rotors front and back. 
 
Scott adds 3 inch wide tires to 27.5 inch wheels to create their amazingly fun and versatile Genius 710 Plus. The result is an all-new bike that will float through sand, fly over loose rocks and cling to corners like nothing before it. Over the last few years we have seen mountain bike wheels grow taller, now they are getting fatter like those on this 27 plus equipped trail tamer. These bigger tires add substantial stability and traction to an already talented full-suspension bike. With superior traction a plus-sized bike makes easy work of rocky climbs and rolls effortlessly down tricky descents while added stability will keep bike, and rider, upright in almost any condition. The Genius 710 Plus features Scott's HMF carbon construction for the mainframe and an alloy swingarm to deliver a fat bike at a light weight and the inclusion of tubeless tires and rims save a bit of weight as well. Not only does the Genius 710 Plus sport the latest wheel size it also comes with a SRAM 11 drivetrain and Reverb dropper post as stock equipment. It's GX1 components use a 10-42 cassette and 30 tooth chainring up front for an impressive range of gears from this simple system. The height-adjustable dropper post allows the rider to put the saddle down and out of the way when negotiating tuff or steep terrain, the seat then pops back into place at the push of a lever. As with other versions of the Genius the 710 Plus uses Fox 34 Float front fork and Fox Nude suspension to add another level of comfort and control to this popular bike. For those wanting all the newness the Scott Genius 710 Plus will quickly become their favorite bike to ride anywhere. 
 
Going on a cross country ride?  No worries, swap out the plus wheels for 29er's (not included) and hit the twinloc from full suspension to half and you're off on a speed racer. 
 
We have S, M or XL currently available.

title: Digi 002 Console mixer
description:
Digidesign 002 console mixer interface. This is an awesome rig. I recorded a shit ton of music on it and it never failed. The only reason I'm selling is because I upgraded to ProTools 11 and has to get a Digi 003 to be compatible.  Its a bummer because this 002 is way better than the 003. Its missing one cap on the knob but it works perfectly. Details below. Does not come with ProTools software. 
 
If the post is up then its still available. Email with questions. 
 
 
Product Details: 
Digi002 - FireWire-Based Music Production System 
Working with your computer through a single FireWire connection, Digi002 pairs with an integrated control surface to provide you with an ideal, finger-friendly music production environment. Record, edit, process, mix, and master your projects with hands-on efficiency, then tuck Digi002 under your arm, take it to a gig, and use it as an 8x4x2 digital mixer complete with EQ, dynamics, delay, and reverb with snapshots. 
Digi002 Basics  
Introducing Digi002, Digidesign's first FireWire-enabled workstation to include an integrated control surface. Digi002 offers novices and pros alike hands-on command of any project, easy connectivity via FireWire and integrated I/O, portability, dual mode functionality, and full session compatibility with other Pro Tools systems, from Mbox to Pro Tools|HD. 
The Essentials 
Digi002 is a full-featured studio-in-a-box that works with your computer to give you all you need for superior MIDI and audio production. Comprised of a single unit that includes a comprehensive control surface along with analog, digital, and MIDI I/O, Digi002 communicates with your computer via a single FireWire cable (included). 
Digi002 System 
Digi002 includes 2 modes of operation: Pro Tools mode, and Standalone mode. With the push of a button, your Digi002 unit enters Standalone mode and becomes an 8x4x2 digital mixer, complete with EQ, dynamics, delay, and reverb with snapshots. In this mode, and your computer is no longer needed for Digi002 to operate. 
With its FireWire connectivity, getting your Digi002 system up and running is comfortably simple. Plug one end of the included FireWire cable into your computer's FireWire port and the other into the Digi002 hardware unit, power up, and you're ready to go. 
FireWire connectivity 
8 touch-sensitive, motorized faders 
8 motion-sensitive rotary encoders used for pan/send/meter/plug-in control 
10 scribble strips for track name, pan, send, fader, plug-in values, and timeline position 
8 channels of Analog I/O 
8 line inputs, 8 line outputs 
4 mic preamps with individual gain and high-pass filter; 48V phantom power enabled on channel pairs 
8 channels of ADAT optical I/O 
2 channels of S/PDIF digital I/O 
Separate monitor output with dedicated volume control 
1 MIDI input and 2 MIDI outputs (16 channels in/32 channels out) 
24-bit/96 kHz A/D and D/A converters 
Stand-alone 8x2 digital mixer mode with EQ, dynamics, and effects 
Alternate Source Input for direct monitoring of -10 dBV audio equipment (tape players, CD players, etc.) 
Headphone output with dedicated volume control knob included 
Dedicated transport control

title: Toyota Tundra  drop-in plastic bedliner
description:
Pt27134070-drop in bed liner for sale. This fits my 2016 crew max Tundra TRD Pro . My truck has the standard 5.5 ft bed with bed rail system. So this bed liner fits all 5.5 ft beds (short bed) on any tundra trim 2007-2016 that has the bed rails system. WILL NOT WORK FOR A TRUCK WITHOUT THE BEDRAIL SYSTEM- There are TWO types of bed liners one for non bedrail track system and one for integrated bedrail track system ; you can email me if you don't understand the difference.  
 
Note: If your truck doesn't have the bed rail system and you still want this bedliner, then you can easily add it, but you have to buy this item separately (~$150) and I am NOT selling mine. Will say though: if you want to add a bedliner, it is really worth it to add bed rail system as it increases the functionality of your truck. 
 
The bedliner was an option included in the truck when I bought it. So I've only had the bedliner in for 6 months now and it is as good as new. Toyota dealer will sell this at 401 + tax (not including install). So they will sell it for ~$440. Get it cheaper here. 
 
FYI: If you have them install it they will charge $539  + tax  (includes bed liner and installation). 
 
This is not a hard part for you to install by yourself (pre-drilled holes in every truck already) - dealers just like to make as much money as they can, wherever they can. 
 
Selling it because my family and I use the truck for camping/outdoors stuff and a bedrug under a Tonneau will go really nicely.

Paid over $400 for these. Will throw them in as its good to have a set of these on the trail in case you ever have an issue.  
 
I've had the truck since day 1 and taken this camping and wheeling a few times a year. I'm selling he truck because I'm getting married and could use the cash to help pay for it. Some times life just comes first. This is a great expedition rig that has pretty much everything you could ask for. This truck as it sits stock is 28-29k and I know I have about and 16k in it. My loss your gain.  
 
Note: I will smog the truck before being release to new owner.  
 
Truck is not my DD so the mile that are on it are only from trips around California and Reno so there are no "hard" miles on this truck. Over all the truck gets about 15MPG highway as it sits. If you choose to re-gear you'll see better mileage and torque, I just never got around to that portion. With this set up the only thing left is gears and lockers.

title: PROMISE Pegasus2 R8 48TB (8 x 6TB) Thunderbolt 2 RAID System
description:
PROMISE Pegasus2 R8 48TB (8 x 6TB) Thunderbolt 2 RAID System 
 
8 Months old. Still under warranty. Working great. 
 
Product Information: 
 
Overview 
 
The premier storage choice for creative audio/video professionals and multimedia enthusiasts around the globe, the PROMISE Pegasus2 now can deliver even faster performance with the new 20 Gb/s Thunderbolt 2 technology, while assuring enterprise-class reliability and ease of use. 
 
Blazing speed for creative workflows 
 
The Pegasus2 is the fastest Thunderbolt 2 storage solution available, delivering raw power for audio/video/graphics amateurs and professionals to experience new capabilities such as easily working with multiple compressed 4K streams. Final Cut professionals can ingest, edit, and play back multiple streams of ProRes 422 (HQ), ProRes4444 as well as uncompressed HD 10-bit and 12-bit video while protecting valuable workflows, audio sessions, and other creative media content. Pegasus2 also works well for popular applications such as iTunes, iPhoto, iMovie, Garageband, Photoshop, and media center applications. 
 
Simple, flexible, and cost-effective backup solutions 
 
Fast, safe, and reliable external storage is essential when protecting your valuable files such as music, photos, and videos. Backup your irreplaceable digital media, documents, and also your entire computer or workstation to Pegasus2 with Time Machine in OS X. 
 
Easy to use, quiet, and eco-smart 
 
Pegasus2 systems are user-friendly, and come pre-configured straight out of the box--so you can just plug in and start using. Status, management tools, and advanced settings can be accessed via the built-in Promise utility. Engineered to be eco-friendly and RoHS compliant, Pegasus2 is perfect for SMB environments. 
 
Enterprise-class RAID protection 
 
Pegasus2 features enterprise-level RAID storage protection for your data, supporting a broad range of RAID levels as well as automatic error handling. 
 
About Thunderbolt 2 
 
Thunderbolt is a revolutionary I/O technology that supports high-resolution displays and high-performance data devices via one simple port and a cable that carries both DisplayPort and PCI Express data. And it's standard on every Mac. 
 
PCI Express is the technology that links all the high-performance components in a Mac. And it's built into Thunderbolt, which means you can get PCI Express speed outside the box. 
 
With Thunderbolt 2 now built into the new Mac Pro and MacBook Pro with Retina display, you can connect up to three 4K displays at once. Thunderbolt 2 gives you up to 20 Gbps in both directions, allowing for super-fast data transfer between peripherals. You also have enough bandwidth to daisy-chain multiple high-speed devices without using a hub or switch. 
 
Thunderbolt also provides double the power of USB 3.0, delivering 10 watts to peripherals for improved performance on the go 
 
Highlights 
 
Choice of raw capacities: 24TB of raw capacity (20.7 TB configured RAID 5 and formatted with HFS+); 32TB of raw capacity (27.9 TB configured RAID 5 and formatted with HFS+); or 48TB of raw capacity (42 TB pre-configured to RAID 5, formatted with HFS+) 
Advanced RAID engine, supports RAID 0, 1, 5, 6, 10 
Robust error handling provides superior data protection 
Reliable, rugged yet elegant enclosure, ultra-quiet design 
Two Thunderbolt 2 ports for daisy chaining up to six Pegasus units, Apple Thunderbolt Displays, or Mini DisplayPort devices 
Hot-swappable bays for effortless drive access and serviceability 
Built-in Promise Utility for systems management and advanced settings 
Backward compatible with 10 Gb/s Thunderbolt hosts and devices 
 
Did You Notice? 
 
Pegasus2 systems come pre-configured straight out of the box--so you can just plug in and start using them. 
 
Apple Recommends For 
 
Take advantage of 20 Gb/s Thunderbolt 2 performance for creative audio/video projects on your Mac Pro.
