title: Native American Flute with lessons in San Mateo - a beginner's dream!
description:
Beginners - you don't need to learn to read or play sheet music in order to play this instrument !! 
 
~ I'll teach you how to play by ear and provide you with all the tools you need in order to quickly learn, play and master this ancient instrument.   
~ I'll teach you a special technique that is unique to playing this flute that will give you the primary skill you need to start playing after just one lesson. . ..watch this Bobby McFerrin video for a hint !!!     
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ne6tB2KiZuk 
 
 
I have a very good selection of Native American Flutes for sale.  They are made by some of the finest craftsmen in the Southwest, who use sustainable woods and a very unique uni-body construction method (these flutes are made from the one piece of wood, unlike most flutes that are made from two pieces of similar wood glued together. . .this creates a more cohesive sound and a flute that will never split apart). 
 
In addition to the flutes listed below I am also offering in person or Skype lessons.  The flutes range in price from $89 to $210 and that means that you can have a world class, crafted instrument in your hand along with all the skills you need to know in order to play a fully improvised song for less than $165!!!. . .Considering the cost of professional ongoing music lessons and the cost of instruments such as the guitar or keyboards this represents a tremendous value! 
 
 
In all my years of playing I have never once read a traditional sheet of music NOR have I used a fingering chart (a visual aid showing you what holes to cover and leave open).  You can play using the more traditional (western) ways and it will eventually enhance your abilities, however, there is a fantastic amount of enjoyment to be had in learning how to create and improvise your own music. Its 100% possible for you to be recording your own music and YouTube videos within 4 weeks of first playing this instrument! 
 
I have been playing this style of flute for over 13 years but I learned to play it in just one afternoon and I'll gladly pass on all the techniques and tips I've picked up over the years.  In particular, and as previously mentioned there is one "secret" technique that aids in mastering this magical instrument and I'm more than happy to share it with you. 
I will teach you how to play this beautiful instrument by ear with a hands on approach WITHOUT you having to learn to read music - There is no need for years of lessons in order to play like a pro!  
 
 
My fateful flute story (short version) - How I learned to play and how you can to! 
It was the week after September the 11th and my sweetheart and I were on a visit to Portland, Oregon.  We were at the Saturday market and a vendor selling his own hand made flutes had set up a stall displaying his wares.  I've been fascinated by this incredible instrument all my life and I had always wanted to play it (I was in my early thirties and wasn't thrilled about having to go through the agony of years of lessons!).  I passed by the flute maker's stall three times before what was once just a whisper in my head of "Gosh I'd love to play that instrument but I just don't have the patience to learn to read music" grew so loud that I decided to stop and admire the flutes and just talk with the seller.  After some initial chit chat the flute maker told me that his flutes were very easy to play and that all I needed was the desire to learn to play and the ability to learn a very simple fingering technique that would allow me to more or less start creating my own songs.  I spent a few minutes listening to him, followed the simple instructions and thankfully followed my gut instinct and bought my very first cedar wood flute!  THANK THE UNIVERSE that I listened to my inner voice that day because I gave myself an incredible gift that has enhanced my life to no end.  That same night while practicing under the stars on the deck of a bed and breakfast overlooking the Hood River Valley I received my very first compliment regarding my flute playing!  I can't imagine my life without music and it's for this very reason that I hope you can enjoy the many riches that come along by playing one of these "magical" flutes. 
 
Sooooo. . . If you 
 
~ Have always had that voice in your head whispering "I'd love to learn to play an instrument BUT....." 
~ Like music but have never taken the step to learn how to play. . . 
~ Have felt overwhelmed by the prospect of having to learn the "rules" of music 
~ Had difficulty with reading or learning 'traditional' music  
~ Tried to learn an instrument but never quite "got the hang of it" 
. . ..then this instrument and my lessons may well be what you've been wishing for all these years !!! 
 
 
Current flutes (CA tax needs to be added to the prices listed below) 
 
~ Birch, tuned to the key of high F#, $89 
~ Birch, tuned to the key of C, $98 
~ Birch, tuned to the key of B, $95 
 
~ Aromatic Cedar, tuned to the key of A, $129 
~ Spanish Cedar, tuned to the key of A, $115 
~ Walnut, tuned to the key of A, $115 
 
~ Aromatic Cedar with Turquoise inlay, tuned to the key of G, $219 
~ Walnut, tuned to the key of G, $159 
 
~ Aromatic Cedar, tuned to F#, $185 
~ Walnut with Turquoise inlay, tuned to F#, $180 
 
~ Spanish Cedar, bass flute tuned to low D, $225 - this has a very deep and soulful 'earth' tone. 
 
~ Individual flute stand, $19 
 
~ One lesson (50 minutes) -- in person in the San Francisco Bay Area or nationwide via Skype - $65.   Follow up lessons can be scheduled IF needed. 
 
Note that the Aromatic Cedar Flute in the key of F# (sharp) makes a distinct sound and tone that most people associate with the Native American Flute and it is one of the finest instruments of any type that you will come across at this price point.  
 
Video clip of flutes for sale;   http://youtu.be/-I12nJh0LtQ 
 
Sound samples of me playing some of the flutes;  https://soundcloud.com/daniel_barry 
 
 
 
I look forward to hearing from you. . ..call/text me on 
  
if you have any questions. 
 
Please note that I've just started this business so a web-site and YouTube videos will follow.

title: 2016 Ridley Orion Di2 Road Bike - Size Medium
description:
Bought this for my daughter and because it was a great deal.  She's not into it.   
 
The Ridley Orion is one of the most versatile bikes in Ridley's line-up. Designed for speed, comfort, and performance, the carbon fiber Orion is perfect for all-day rides, gran fondos, and anyone who wants to get more out of every ride. 
The Orion frame tubes are diamond shaped for strength and durability, while the geometry and taller headtube promise plenty of comfort and exceptionally stable handling. According to Ridley, the bike offers "comfort, stiffness, and strength in equal measure", but this is no take-it-easy weekend path and pavement bike. This is one of the toughest, race-ready bikes (it even has the UCI approval sticker on the downtube, for extra legit-ness) you'll find anywhere, with plenty of get-up and go. It also just happens to deliver an amazingly comfortable ride as well. 
 
The frame is made with high modulus unidirectional carbon fiber formed into Ridley's distinctive diamond shape for rugged strength and durability. The taller headtube both alleviates stress on the lower back while riding and enhances frame stiffness by eliminating the need to use as many headset spacers. 
 
The carbon fiber fork features a medium rake that gives the bike the ability to dive into turns without feeling twitchy or unstable. The carbon fiber arms and alloy steerer help absorb road vibrations and smooth out the ride. 
 
For 2016, the Orion comes with a Shimano Ultegra Di2 6870 groupset. With Di2, Changing gears has never been so easy, effortless and fast. Ultegra Di2 features an automatic trimming front derailleur, so you never have to hear the sound of chain rub again. The shifters act with digital push button shifting and are ergonomically shaped for optimal comfort and control. The lever reach adjust fits all hand sizes. The Di2 rear derailleur is pre-programmed allowing you to shift gear quickly and accurately in all conditions. The battery, at the heart of the drivetrain, uses lithium ion technology and guarantees a range of 1,250 miles, or almost half the length of the Tour de France, before it needs to be recharged, which only takes just 90 minutes. 
Rounding out this impressive package is a build kit from Ridley's own 4Za brand. 4Za is in many ways unlike some other company's house brand component arms. Ridley engineers every 4Za component to integrate seamlessly with their bikes at a basic level, ensuring optimized performance at every level. The bike rolls on a set of lightweight Alex Rims clinchers, which spin up quickly, climb like they mean it, and deliver superb braking performance. 
 
 
Features: 
 
Developed with input from the pro-tour level Damocles and Excalibur frames 
Unique Ridley fit utilizes a traditional geometry and taller headtube, so you need fewer spacers, creating a stiffer, more stable frame 
High modulus carbon fiber makes the Orion stiff when you stand up out of the saddle on hard efforts, but allows more compliance for comfort on long rides 
Diamond-shaped tubing makes the Orion stronger and more durable 
Shimano Ultegra Di2 6870 11-speed electronic drivetrain will revolutionize the way you ride

Bianchi 928 Carbon SL is a super-light carbon monocoque frame applies nanotechnology to tune the carbon material at micro dimensions, delivering a ride that transcends handling, efficiency, and compliance boundaries. You'll experience race-ready solidity like never before and luxuriate in the 928 Carbon SL's instant responsiveness and vibration absorption; all at a frame weight of a feathery 860 grams (medium frame)! title: 1995 Grey BMW 325i OBO (Not passing Smog)
description:
Hey CL, up for sale is my 1995 BMW 325i (premium package when it ws bought), it's currently not passing smog for the second time due to high Hydrocarbons and is being sold as is. I will non op it at the end of the month.  
The car runs great and I'm not sure why it's not passing, it could be as simple as an 02 sensor or as bad the engine being worn or the catalytic converters (but I don't think so) , I'm not sure so..my loss could be your gain.  I'm currently a student and I using it purely for commuting back and forth and shopping and things like that, I've never raced it. I've always taken good care of it I've owned the car since 145k and I've always used 91 from either Costco or the Chevron and let it warm up for a couple minutes everytime before I drive it. It has always been on a full synthetic oil and currently is on relatively new oil at around 4k miles on it. It has some issues but none of them relate to actual performance or safety of the car and would be an easy fix for anyone car savvy, I'd say they are expected for a car that's from the mid 90's.  
 
Pro's 
- the engine pulls hard and feels really strong, honestly I've driven other 325i's and mine is really peppy. 
-new oem copper plated spark plugs 
-new Myle HD control arms with heavy duty ball joints 
-new Myle HD front brake lines & new brake fluid/flush  
-new allignment 
-new struts (can't remember the name atm) 
-new pcv breather hose 
-newish full synthetic oil 
-new radiator expansion tank 
-newish air filter 
-newish cabin filter 
-newish transmission fluid 
-new passenger side rear strut mount 
-newish tires 
 
Cons 
-Clutch at 25% life but grabs strong and has no signs of giving out soon 
-Not passing smog  
-ABS light on just because of a malfunctioning sensor on the right front side (easy fix I just havent gotten around to it yet). 
-Was keyed in the past before I owned it but only on one side 
-hood is oxidizing in the center and it's noticeable (rest of the paint looks good) 
-passenger side windshield wiper no longer workers 
-drivers side window doesn't track correctly/ is broken so I keep it closed (motor workers however) 
-lights that show mileage don't work (they come once but then went away...not sure whats up but you can easily see the mileage) 
-drivers side seat upper portion back adjustment gear is broken so the seat doesn't recline BUT it's stuck in the perfect position..go figure haha. 
-drivers seat has a tear in the bottum portion where you sit BUT it has never englarged since I've owned it or have I ever felt it while driving. 
 
The car is my DD and is definitely not perfect but it looks nice and is a clean car (will post pictures soon) I've decided to get a much new car after owning it for over a year. It would be a great DD for any student and/or someone who doesn't mind doing some work to get it into tip top shape. I'm open to offers so if interested shoot me a message. Thanks for looking!

Hollister Powersports Your South Bay Honda Dealer  
 
 
Explore Your World  
 
You probably know someone like this. Maybe it's your brother-in-law, or your neighbor, or some guy at your workplace. He's always telling you what he's going to do . . . but he never really does anything. But there's another kind of guy too--someone who turns every day into something that's fun. Every weekend he comes back with a story to tell, even if he never crossed a state line. 
 
Honda's new VFR®1200X is built for people who know adventure isn't someplace you go, it's what you do getting there. It's an excellent machine for exploring the world around you, and doing it in comfort, confidence, and style. Sporty, athletic, nimble enough for around-town cruising or tight winding back roads, it's also big enough to reel in those highway miles, and see the Statue of Liberty, Mount Rushmore, and the Alamo all in the same trip.

title: 2009 Mercedes Benz AMG SL63
description:
I am selling my heavily optioned 2009 Mercedes-Benz SL63 produced by AMG in Affalterbach, Germany. I bought the vehicle in March 2014 with 27,000 miles, it currently has 33,500 miles on the odometer.  
 
This car is in excellent condition -- always garaged and always protected with a car cover when parked outdoors. This is a weekend cruising car perfect for trips down Pacific Coast highway or a top-down jaunt through the city. The V8 engine has immense torque and a low, guttural growl that isn't too aggressive- together with the upgraded suspension package and wider tires makes for exciting highway on-ramps and runs down Skyline Drive.  
 
This SL63 has never been in an accident and does not need any maintenance.  
Standard SL63 options include: 
- Hand-built 6.3L V8 engine producing 518 horsepower/465 lb-ft torque (car came from the factory with a DVD of its engine being built) 
- 7 speed dual clutch manumatic transmission (0.100 sec shifts in manual control mode) with paddle shifters and three driving modes 
-14.2 inch 6-piston ventilated front brakes and 13.0 inch 4-piston ventilated rear brakes 
- AMG Sport Exhaust 
- 19" Wheels with 255/35 front and 285/30 rear Michelin Pilot Sport Pro tires 
- Automatic retracting hardtop that works flawlessly- no binding, hesitation, or issues. No repairs ever needed to this mechanism. 
- 12-way adjustable heated, massaging seats with memory (perfect condition -- no scratches, scuffs, or wear present) 
- Alcantara headliner (in perfect condition) 
- 6-disc stereo-navigation system with 40GB hard drive, Bluetooth connectivity, and voice command. Harmon-Kardon speakers still in perfect condition -- no fading drivers. Sirius satellite radio compatible -- though I never used it.  
- iPhone/mobile audio connection in center console (works with iPhones 4, 5, and 6) -- includes stereo jack for any other portable audio device.  
 
Original MSRP was $159,675, including $21,200 in additive options: 
- Option 219 -- Parktronic: Sensor-assist front and rear collisions detection 
- Option 220 - Distronic: Adaptive Cruise Control  
- Option 033 - Designo interior in Mocha Black (pearlescent medium brown highlights that show up really well in bright sunlight) 
- Option 217 - Red AMG Premium Leather 
- Option H73 - Carbon Fiber trim package (interior and exterior carbon elements) 
- Option 030 - AMG Performance Package including: 19" AMG forged alloy wheels, AMG Limited Slip Differential (LSD), Track-calibrated Active Body Control (ABC) suspension system, AMG performance steering wheel (hollow alloy spokes and flat bottom), increased governing speed to 186mph 
- Suspension lifts to clear obstacles and steep grades in the road 
- Suspension has Comfort (suppresses rough road conditions) and Sport (aggressively enhances handling capability) driving modes which are really significant, unlike many German sports cars where these modes only make minor changes.  
- Option P01 - Premium Package, consisting of: activated ventilated (heated and cooled) seats, electronic trunk closer, Airscarf (heated headrest blower), and Keyless Go (push-button start and keyless entry) 
 
The engine is in mint condition. I never experienced any hesitation or detonation; it doesn't burn any oil or knock on startup. The motor pulls strong through the rev range. Transmission shifts rapidly every time. I have not had a single repair needed since I purchased the vehicle. I never saw any DTC records appear (check engine light).   
 
Interior is in mint condition. All electronic systems work perfectly and I know it connects with iPhone generations 4, 5 and 6.  
 
Exterior is in excellent condition -- there is one minor blemish on the front fender that was present when I bought it in March of 2014. Paint is in excellent condition -- I wax and clay block it regularly. I replaced the lower lip on front bumper due to scratches from the occasional steep driveway.  
 
The 2009 SL63 is a well-built car produced after the breakup of DaimlerChrysler (often noted for the reduced build quality of Mercedes Benz vehicles under their reign) and has no Recalls, Investigations, or Complaints according to the National Highway Transportation Administration (NHTSA: www.safercar.gov).  
 
This car, like most used vehicles sold privately, is sold as-is with no implied or expressed warranty. Buyer may have the vehicle inspected at their own cost at a reputable local mechanic.  
 
At this time, I am not interested in trades. Serious buyers only please.

title: 1970 VW Beetle
description:
READ the whole ad 1st.  It should answer the vast majority of your questions.  Last 2 weeks then pulling the ad down (will be up later, but will be stripped of all the good parts...will only have stock parts).  Not interested in parting the car out.  What ever doesn't go with the car goes to the next project.  Pics are older but the car looks the same just with fenders on the front and no rear bumper. Here's the details on my 70:  
 
BODY:  
 
In great shape with no accident damage that I can see. Paint is dull but it shines up really well. Has pop-out rear windows, stock door windows, windshield is perfect and the rear window has no defrost strips. Is missing the running boards and bumpers. I've changed out the front fenders with a set from a pre-67 with glass lenses (fenders are primered and the headlight units are brand new aftermarket units with 911 lenses). I've installed a set of GAB FAB carb windows in the rear quarters (fantastic quality). The only problems is the engine firewall has some bad welding and there is 1 spot of rust on the front driver side quarter panel (about 1" x 3" long). (1) key opens the doors and works the ignition.  
 
PAN/SUSPENSION: Pans have been coated with POR-15. Passenger side pan was replaced by BuggyHouse in Hayward with a unit from Wolfsburg West. Front beam is a 2" adjustable narrowed unit from CB Performance with everything except for the steering box replaced. Has (4) wheel discs in a stock 4x130 pattern (by CB Performance). All brake hard lines have been replaced with lines from Wolfsburg West with S/S soft lines. Master cylinder is a German unit with a 2lb residual valve. Brakes and the ebrake work like the should. But, could use a tiny bit of bleeding ((almost have it perfect)).  Rims are 4 lug BRM's with caps and new tires.  Everything has only 20 miles (towed....not driven). I also have a narrowed front sway bar (brand new) that need the clamps to install. Pedal cluster has been rebuilt with a classicbugparts gas, pedal and clutch arm upgrade, Shift rod has been lubed and has a new bushing and black urethane coupler installed. Needs the clutch tube welded back up (makes a sound when you push in the clutch).  
 
INTERIOR: Black vinyl Procar Pro-90 front seats with the correct mounts. Driver seat and both seat mounts are brand new. The passenger seat is used but in excellent condition. There is no back seat. Dash is cracked but there. Door cards are there and are in good shape. Speedometer is a later unit that has been cleaned up and reset to 0 miles (not installed).  Steering wheel is a 73 Sports bug steering wheel in good shape.  Shifter is a Scat dragfast with a custom red billard ball handle. Glove box is a new ABS unit. Wiring has been somewhat cleaned up but needs to be finished up from the battery to engine. Wiring is there....you just need to feed it thru the quarter panel and into the engine bay.  
 
ENGINE/TRANSMISSION:  
 
(2) engines available:  1- Engine is a 1600 and was from a 77 beetle.  Its been sitting for awhile but was running fine before removal.  I've had all the tin powdercoated and made a set of cylinder deflectors below the heads.  Alternator and cooling fan are brand new.  Carbs are 40 IDFs, case was full-flowed and has a 30mm oil pump, in and out cover and a CB performance 1-1/2 qt sump.  Ignition is by bosch blue coil and 009 with pertronix (electric ignition).  Heads are Los Banditos from CB performance with 40mm intake and 35mm exhaust.  Mileage on the engine is unknown and no warranty on it. 
 
The other engine is a brand new long block 1641.  Has all new parts:  26mm oil pump, in/out cover, full-flow, resurfaced flywheel, 100 cam, new I or H beam rods, bearings and case machined to .40, and brand new stock heads.  Its was ran on the stand but either I had a bad sensor, wrong oil weight or something happened and the oil light flickered while in break-in.  It was promptly shut down and set aside.  I've not torn it down but, it cost $1400 so, you can easily get your money worth by either figuring out what is wrong, selling it or parting it out.  I will sell either 1 motor or both or none at all.   
 
Please note:  the billet carb filters, linkage, header and serpentine pulleys pictured are NOT included and are not optional. I have a replacement carb filter set that I will include.  The transmission is a 3:88 aka "freeway flyer" that was working good prior to me buying it.  The tranny mounts are german and are brand new. 
 
Will come with some new/used parts: Fender beading in black, misc seals, 2-1/2" disc brake drop spindles (used), spare front windshield, Engine bay firewall section, Fuel tank, beetle tow bar (needs to be narrowed or bent to fit on the narrowed front beam) and a few other little odds and ends.  
 
I have the title in my name. Car is setup on non-op with no back fees at all.  I'm willing to sell the car a few different ways....but no negotiating....prices are FIRM, no other options: 
 
-Without the motor, wheels, brake calipers, steering wheel and transmission $1000 (bring your own wheels and steering wheel) 
-Without the motor $1600 (as it sits currently) 
-With the 1641 motor (longblock only) $2000 
-With the 1600 motor (longblock only) $2000 
-With the 1600 motor (minus the carbs, manifolds, alternator and stand) $2200  
-With the 1600 motor $2600 
-With both engines $3000 
 
Trades....I'm looking for either a 71-72 factory sunroof super or 73 thru 75 sunroof or hardtop super or 69 and up Ghia. Would like a light color car (white, tan, baby blue or yellow). MUST be factory paint....not interested in primer buckets (might consider primer if its a ghia). Don't need a motor, but must have a working transmission (or we can swap mine out).  MUST have title in your name and either non-op'd or current registration.

title: 2000 GMC Sierra 1500 4x4
description:
I am selling my 2000 gmc sierra 1500. Its been my truck for the past year and I love it, but unfortunately have to let it go to pay some bills off.  
 
The truck is in great running condition. I knew the previous owner and know he took well care of the truck with on time oil changes as well as transmission flushed, as did I. Like i said, ive had it for about a year now and never had any problems. It has the Vortec 5.3L V8. Under the hood is almost spotless.  
 
The truck has 4 wheel drive, which is a definate plus. Always nice to have just in case. The 4x4 works great, never any issues. In regular 2 wheel drive it rides smooth, shifts smooth, and sounds great with its 30 series flowmaster exhaust.  
 
Other random perks that come with the truck are include, a custom Rhino Lined subwoofer box fitted with 2 12" pro comp kickers under the back seat. An aftermarket Pioneer stereo, with aftermarket speakers all the way around. The bed of the truck is Rhino Lined not only once, but twice for extra durability. It also has brand new mud terrain tires. The back three windows are tinted. 
 
Like any older truck, it does have its normal wear and tear, like the driver seat has a small rip on it, and there are minor scratches here an there.  
 
Thanks for looking, if you are interested please call or shoot me a text. Names Michael.

description:
Testing the waters and in no rush to sell.   
 
Clean title, 1998 BMW M3 Sedan, 5 speed in Cosmos Schwartz Metallic with black leather interior.  Rare M3 sedan with manual transmission and folding rear seats.   Car has been well cared for by both the previous owner and me since we are both enthusiasts.  It pulls hard, handles extremely well, and the interior is in excellent shape (no rips or tears on the leather). Come check it out and you will not be disappointed.  Trust me, six years ago I went to see it out of curiosity, but came away so impressed that I bought it.  Fast-forward to now and I still thoroughly enjoy it each time I drive it.  Wife prefers a newer car, but we'll see if this gets replaced. 
 
I have owned this vehicle since 2010 and have a folder full of records.  The previous owner owned it since 2001, when he bought it from eleasereturns.com.  He is an airline mechanic, so he performed all the maintenance himself, other than the clutch replacement.  He treated the car extremely well and it had tons of sentimental value to him and his wife.  He filmed me as I drove away in it.  When you see the Carfax report, you will see the clean title and two out of state stints during the previous owners ownership period (Illinois and Washington).   I verified (via LinkedIn) that both of those out of state periods corresponded with the previous owners employment history at different airlines. 
 
During my ownership the following has been performed: 
-	Valve cover gasket replacement twice.  10/16 was the most recent 
-	Oil changes with Mobil 1 5w-30 every 3,000 miles.  10/16 
-	New NGK Laser Platinum spark plugs (BKR6EQUP 3199) for smog.  03/16 
-	PFC 08 Compound Racing Brake Pads (a lot of life left) & new cross-drilled rotors.  02/16 
-	All fluids flushed. 02/16 
-	AC compressor, tensioner, and recharge 06/16 
-	New shifter boot, shift bushing, driveshaft flex joint 02/16. 
-	Michelin Pilot Super Sport tires  
-	Cooling system overhaul with Mishimoto Radiator, new water pump, thermostat, drive belts, etc. 
-	Pioneer DEH-80PRS Deck with CD, Bluetooth, and remote.  Infinity Kappa 693.9i rear speakers. 
-	BMW ZHP Shift knob 
-	BMW parking brake lever 
-	Front driver window regulator 
-	Driver side rear door lock actuator 
-	New replacement front driver side wheel well plastic trim 
-	New front tie rods 
-	New front & rear windshield 
-	New trunk shocks 
-	New gear for front driver seat back adjustment 
-	Stock spare tire purchased 
-	New headliner 
-	New coin holder 
-	Depo HID 5k headlights.  Orange Corner lights and side markers. 
-	Dime sized ding on the trunk was repaired by dentless pro. 
 
Other modifications on the car: 
-	Active Autowerke Cold Air Intake (Stock one included) 
-	Active Autowerke Exhaust 
-	BMW X-Brace 
-	Bilstein Shocks 
-	H&R Sport Springs 
-	BBS RG-R 19x8.5 wheels 
-	RTABs 
-	E46 Rear Shock Mounts 
-	New clutch 
-	Stainless steel brake lines 
-	TMS brake bushings 
-	JTD Underpanel 
-	JL Audio 600 Watt amp for speakers 
-	MB Quart front separate speakers 
-	10 inch Alpine Type R Sub, driven by 300 watt Alpine Amp 
-	Fan delete mod 
 
Full disclosure, so here's some additional history on the car. 
-	Matching VIN's on all four doors, trunk, and in engine compartment.  Previous owner was never in an accident.  Only minor accident I have been in was last year.  Someone hit my rear bumper at I would say 5-10mph.  I was stopped at a light and he could not stop in time.  Very minimal damage, which insurance covered.  I have provided a picture of it in the ad.  Just the rear bumper was replaced. 
-	I have tracked the car once in March of last year.  My first time on the track and it was through Hooked on Driving with an instructor.  Loved the car at the track and it is far more capable than what I put it through.  I had a lot of fun and plan to go to more track events but have not been able to again. 
-	Previous owner never tracked the car, since he took his motorcycle to the track instead.  PPI performed by Edge Motorworks when I purchased it and they confirmed it. 
-	195,XXX miles on it currently. 
-	OBC fully functional, as you can see from the photo provided.  No issues whatsoever. 
-	Service manual included along with spare/new parts (oil filter, relay, window washer hose, stock air intake, stock fan, and anything else I can dig up). 
-	There is a small leak at the steering rack, which my mechanic was comfortable having me go to the track with in March.  It's still just a small leak. 
-	There are rock chips on the hood and the clear coat has peeled between the headlights and kidney grills.  I have provided a picture of it.  Bought the car like this. 
-	There is a small door ding on the driver side rear door. 
-	Passenger side A-Pillar interior trim is loose when an older family member reached for it thinking there was a handle. 
-	Passenger side Angel Eye does not light up. 
-	Fog lights do not turn on.  I rarely use them.  It is not the light bulbs (PIAA yellows) and it is not the relay (have a new spare one).  
-	I have a replacement windshield washer hose, which I have not had time to replace. 
-	The sun roof tilts up (which is all I use it for), but do not open it all the way.  Otherwise you will have to crank it closed.  Bought the car like this. 
 
I am asking $7,900 or best offer.  Don't waste my time and yours.  Come take a look at the car first.  Smog and title in hand.

title: 1966 Mustang - supercharged, fuel injected, quick!
description:
Up for sale is my 1966 Ford Mustang Coupe.  I've owned this car since 1995, and over the years transformed it from a humble, low performance dud to a fire breathing monster.  I have a lot of blood, sweat, and money in this car, and while it is tough to let it go, it's time for someone else to have fun with it. 
 
Originally a 289/4speed, it now sports a supercharged, fuel injected, 331 cubic inch engine with a 5 speed manual trans.  This is not your average Mustang - this car was built for street and strip and is rediculously quick and powerful.  Everything on the car is new or restored and built with the best products on the market.  Over $60K invested, with the receipts to prove it. One ride and you'll be hooked.  It's fast, loud, reliable, and will rip your head off. There are far too many modifications to list, but here are the highlights: 
 
The Car: 
1966 Mustang Coupe - stripped to bare metal and repainted in 2000 in Autumn Orange 
Professionally fabricated and installed 6-point roll bar and subframe connectors 
Cal-Tracs traction bars 
Heidt's Mustang II front end with tubular A-arms 
Manual rack and pinion steering 
JBA Headers, 2-1/2 exhaust with x-pipe, Flowmaster 40 series mufflers 
Aeromotive A1000 fuel pump, Aeromotive regulator and fuel rails 
Stainless steel fuel tank by Rick's Tanks 
Budnik Fontana billet wheels -16x8 
205/55R16 front, 225/55R16 rear BFG G-force tires 
JME Instrument panel with Autometer Sportcomp gauges 
Ford EEC-IV Engine Management with TWEECER programmable module (laptop included) 
Ford Racing Wiring Harness 
Optima Red top battery, trunk mounted, with shutoff switch - NHRA legal 
Rear seat firewall 
Ford 9" rear with 3.50:1 gears, Detroit Locker, Strange 31-spline axles 
Front and rear disk brakes

title: Eurocom Sky X9 - 17" FHD / i7 6700K / GTX 980M 8GB / SSD / 16 GB RAM
description:
Hi guys, 
 
I am parting with the best (desktop replacement) laptop that I have ever owned: Eurocom Sky X9. I am letting it go because now I will be permanently based in California and I can finally migrate full time to an actual desktop system. 
 
I have been taking very good care of the laptop. (One could say it was babied.) It comes from a smoke-free home. The rig is well built and the internals are very easy to access (see album pictures at http://imgur.com/a/DTR9r ) should you want to upgrade any components or just clean it inside. 
 
The panel is flawless, no dead pixels, no light bleeding on the sides. The images are vivid. (I actually like this display even more than that of my previous Alienware 17.) The keyboard and palm rest area are in excellent condition, as is the chassis. The only side that will show signs of wear is the lid -- there are some light scratches along the sculpted edges (which do not affect the laptop's functionality in any way); the laptop is black with non-reflective finish, so the mentioned cosmetic blemishes are not immediately visible. (I encourage you to look closely at all the pictures here: http://imgur.com/a/DTR9r - I tried my best to get shots with good details for you.) Also notable: the battery wear is only 3%, which means it is virtually as good as new. 
 
Here are the most relevant specs: 
 
   
EUROCOM Sky X9 
 
  		 
17.3-inch (43.9cm); FHD IPS 1920x1080; MATTE (Non-Glare); 300nts; 700:1 
 
 		 
8GB GDDR5; NVIDIA GTX 980M (N16E-GX);  ; 1536 CUDA; MXM 3.0b; 100W; 
 
  		 
4GHz (up to 4.2GHz) Intel Core i7-6700K; 4C/8T; 8MB L3; Skylake-S; 14nm; LGA1151; 91W 
 
  		 
16GB; 2x 8GB; DDR4; 2400Hz; CL14; 260-pin; 1.2V; Kingston HyperX Impact; 2 SODIMMs 
 
  	 
256GB SSD; MLC; Micron M600; SATA3 6Gb/s; 7mm 
 
 		        
 Microsoft Windows 10 Professional; 64-bit 
 
 	 
Backlit; English; (customizable)  
 
 	 
6-in-1 Card Reader; MMC/RSMMC/SD/MiniSD/SDHC/SDXC; UHS-II interface 
 
  	 
2-in-1; 802.11a/b/g/n/ac WLAN + Bluetooth 4.1; Killer Wireless-AC 1525; M.2 223 
 
 	 
2.0 Megapixels; Built-in 
 
 	 
Sound Blaster X-Fi MB5; external 7.1CH audio output; headphone out, microphone in, S/PDIF and Line-in port; two built-in FORSTER Speakers (2.2W) + Subwoofer (2.5W) 
 
 		 
1x USB 3.1 type C (HDMI 2.0/DP 1.2/Thunderbolt 3); 2x miniDP 1.2; 1x HDMI 2.0; 5x USB 3.0 (1x Powered USB AC/DC); S/PDIF; Headphone; Mic; Line-in; 2x RJ45 (LAN) 
 
 		 
8-cells Smart Li-lon Battery; internal; 
 
 		 
WxDxH 428x308x45mm / 17.12x12.32x1.8-inch 
 
 	 
4.8kg / 10.56lbs  
 
 	 
330 W 
 
 
Additional features include: 
 
Prema BIOS 
Two 1Gb LAN RJ-45 ports Killer E2400 + M.2 WLAN/Bluetooth; Killer DoubleShot X3 
Built-in Fingerprint Reader 
Embedded TPM 2.0 Security Chip for Data Encryption 
IC Diamond 7 Carat Thermal Compound cooling on CPU and GPU 
 
 
 
I would like to emphasize this model's huge selling points (at least, in my view): 
 
 
 
 
i7-6700K is already the most powerful 6th gen processor on the consumer market, yet you can squeeze even more out of it. It's all under your control given the Prema BIOS provides access to multiple very fine system tweaks. (But you do have to know what you are doing, of course!) This is an invaluable boon for all those who need the extra horsepower in CAD, CDD, or video editing applications. 
 
 
 
 
This is not a typo -- 64 GB (4 x 16GB); this system sports 4 SODIMM sockets (all quite easy to access). If you are a gamer, then that's overkill obviously. If your line of work or hobby involves working in CAD applications with massive 3D models and animation, or DCC software such as Adobe Premiere Pro, After Effects, Speedgrade, Illustrator, Photoshop and their multiple plugins, then 64 GB RAM is no longer a ridiculous number -- playback and rendering times even for hi-def+ content are simply unheard of on this mobile platform. 
 
 
 
 
This will mean a lot to enthusiast gamers. I don't really play many titles, mainly DOTA 2, and to me, the G-Sync feature makes a world of difference, esp. when the game remains smooth even when I pan across very crowded battle scenes and there is no stuttering or screen tearing. I used to think G-Sync is more of a marketing thing, but it is as good as they all hailed it to be. 
 
 
 
 
That means you can add another GPU and have two NVidia GeForce video cards in SLI. I will include the SLI cable if you wish. 
 
 
 
 
You can migrate to a desktop GPU anytime if you so desire; although I would recommend going for the SLI 980M configuration since it is significantly more powerful than a single desktop GPU (besides, there is a mobile GPU installed already) 
 
 
 
 
Okay, whether it is for play or for work this laptop can be the cornerstone of your dream setup with all the possible ports for accommodating any needs you may have. Configuring outputs is very easy and straightforward through NVidia Control panel. 
 
 
 
 
Again, whether you work or play, the capabilities of this new generation of SSDs are mind-boggling. Look at the stats yourselves: 
http://www.anandtech.com/show/7843/testing-sata-express-with-asus/4 
 
 
 
 
The Prema BIOS mod enables the user to customize every little thing in this system, from whether you want the manufacturer logo to appear onscreen at startup, to CPU and RAM overclocking, voltage alterations, to when to start and stop charging the battery. 
 
 
I think I could fill pages with what I like about this laptop. It is truly unique and it is not built for your mainstream user. I tried to provide as much info as possible so that you can have a better picture when you compare the different models you have in mind and all the benefits one gets you over the other. If I left any questions unanswered, please feel free to write to me and I will try to get back to you as soon as reasonably possible. 
 
Here are hi-res pics of the actual unit for sale: http://imgur.com/a/DTR9r 
 
Good luck! 
 
P.S. In-person deals only. Not interested in trades.

title: JBL Dual 15" Speakers and QSC GX7 Amp
description:
Excellent dual 15" JBL TR-225 Speakers, 1000W each. Come with matching QSC GX7 power amp, 1000W per side, 2000W total. One of the best sounding speakers around. They are actually 3-way: 15" drivers are the same, but tuned differently, one for bass, one is shifted towards midrange. Because of that the transition from LF to HF is smoother, they sounds much better than a typical 2-way speaker and even some 3-way speakers. 
 
Standalone amp is much more efficient than any built-in amp module of a powered speaker. There are no size and weight restrictions, plus very efficient cooling utilizing large fan. You will never have any overheat problems common to powered speakers. FYI, large arena-sized sound systems, like JBL VerTec, consists entirely of passive speakers driven by standalone amps. They even use separate amps to drive LF and HF drivers. Passive speakers is the way to go in a pro world. 
 
Price is for a set, two speakers and one amp. I have two of these identical sets, two amps and four speakers total, together they make an excellent main PA for a band, club, church, etc. Two speakers per side, powered from the same amp in mono mode, pretty much like powered speakers because amps are placed right next to speakers, cables are short. I carried the whole band's PA in a short body Ford Aerostar minivan: these JBLs go at the back, 4 QSC K12 monitors take the middle seat and mixer goes on a front passenger's seat. 
 
Considering the size and sound output, you are practically getting each speaker for half of cost of similar size powered speaker (they are in $1000-plus range each, even used). You can have 4000W of raw power for under $3K (using both of my sets). None of powered speakers can match it. 
 
Speakers are in excellent condition, can be tested any way you want. I have a mixer available to test. Since you see this ad now, it means that speakers are STILL AVAILABLE.

title: Mackie DL1608 Digital Mixer with Wi-Fi Router
description:
Digital mixer of the year, the ultra-compact 16-channel 8-bus Mackie DL-1608. Wireless remote control from iPad and iPhone from anywhere in the venue, ton of features that doesn't exist in other analog and digital mixers, and all this fits in a standard laptop bag! 
 
- Excellent ONYX mic preamps, the same as in ONYX-80 series large format analog mixers and ONYX recording interfaces. Accept ANY signal source, from condenser mics to line-level (keyboards, digital drums, iPhone/iPod, CD player, etc.) 
- Full digital control, including scenes memory and recall.  
- 4-band fully parametric EQ and full dynamics suite (compressor, limiter, gate, expander) on each and every input and output. 
- Eight 31-band graphic equalizers with +/- 15dB range (more than typical 12dB), also with unique "Draw" feature (let you draw a desired EQ curve right on iPad, instead of moving each slider separately). 
- Two independent effects processors with all the stuff you may need for a gig: reverbs, delays, etc. 
- Channels and effects preset libraries. Real time saver, you can load typical preset like "Kick drum", "Piano", "Guitar", Female VOX", etc, it gets 90% of job done, then you can tweak it to your taste. 
- Instant one-button two-track or multi-track recording straight to iPad. You can record your event as multitrack session and later polish it in a studio with any DAW (ProTools, Logic, Cubase, etc.) 
- Remote levels control from any iPhone or iPod Touch. You can let musicians dial their own monitor mixes (up to 6 independent mono mixes). This feature is a lifesaver, no more "I can't hear myself in monitors" or "I need more of this and that"). In fact you are getting a full functionality of an Aviom personal monitor mixers for free: everyone has an iPhone today, all you need is to download a free app! 
 
DL1608 can easily handle a typical 4-5 piece band gig (most bands fit into 16-channel grid, even with fully miked drum kit, and never need more than 6 separate monitor mixes). I've done plenty of cover bands with this mixer. 
 
Too many features to list here, read online reviews or download MasterFader app to your iPad and try it in demo mode, it's awesome! New version 4.0 adds bunch of new features: custom channel layers, VCAs, 6-band parametric EQ on outputs, etc. etc.  
 
Also watch MasterFader launch video: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4yCGH5mmGaU 
 
The most comprehensive video tutorial on DL1608 covering the latest MasterFader 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_0OnElTV5oo 
It's an hour long, but covers EVERYTHING, definitely worth watching at least once. 
 
This is 30-pin dock version (for iPad 1 and 2). Can be used with any iPad model, from Mini to Pro (for newer iPads with Lighting connector you can use a 30-pin-to-Lighting adapter ($29 from Apple Store or around $6 on eBay), or just use Wi-Fi connection. (Note that all other iPad-controlled mixers on the market doesn't even have a dock for iPad, Wi-Fi only!). Mixer hardware is identical in both, so they sounds the same. All the sound processing is done inside of DL-1608, iPad is just the controller (also, if you'll lose Wi-Fi connection to the mixer, nothing will happen, it will still pass audio in the state it was left on). 
 
Mixer is in excellent condition, everything works 100%. Selling only the mixer with power supply, iPad is shown just for illustration, how it looks together. Works with all iPad models. Comes with Linksys wireless router, all set up and ready to go. Make sure to download MasterFader app to your iPad before coming if you want to test it (it's also a good way to learn mixer in offline mode). I can test functionality with my iPad if desired. It doesn't take a lot of iPad computing power to work, so the older iPads work fine, and those are dirt cheap today ($100-130 for iPad 2, there's about 400 of them for sale on Craigslist at the moment). 
 
Since you see this ad now, it means the mixer is STILL AVAILABLE

Like the aluminum "Unibody" models, this system also has a four-finger "multi-touch" glass trackpad and an integrated battery design that is not intended to be replaced by the end user. title: 2011 Libtech Travis Rice 164cm
description:
2011 Libtech Travis Rice. Used but not abused. Great shape. Base has one area that has scratches but does not affect performance. Bindings NOT included. $200 
 
 
http://www.evo.com/outlet/snowboards/lib-tech-t-rice-pro-model-c2btx-banana-rocker-snowboard.aspx 
 
Lib Tech T. Rice Pro Model C2BTX Banana Rocker Snowboard 2011: The Lib Tech T. Rice Pro Model C2BTX Banana Rocker Snowboard is Travis' go-to stick when he is droppin' the big air for which we know him so well. Take the pointy pow-specific nose and a stiffer flex pattern for increased pop and stability and go chow down on some freshies.  
 
FLEX 
 
Flex rating: 7 (1 Soft -- 10 Stiff). Features C2 Power Banana which is designed for aggressive all terrain freestyle riders. Banana Tech rocker between your feet combined with cambers at each end of the board. 
 
CONSTRUCTION AND CORE 
 
Made with Axis inversion fiberglass featuring an H-Pop Wood Alloy Core that gives the highest compression response ever, with half the glue weight and absorbs less resin weight absorption. 
 
The C2 Banana Rocker combination offers the best features of Banana Tech. . .float in powder in both directions, carving on hardpack and ice and a catchfree freestyle performance with the best features of camber. . .end to end stability, and extra pop for strong aggressive riders. 
 
Slightly pointed tip and tail with sparkly shiny Bio-plastic topsheet made from beans finish. 
 
SHAPE 
 
Twin pointy pow shape (161.5, 164.5) & Twin blunt jib shape (153, 157). 
 
SIDEWALLS, EDGES AND BASE 
 
Magne-Traction serrated edges features 7 bumps strategically placed along the sidecut, with the largest bumps at and between your feet to add maximum control and power where you need it most. Magne-Traction shifts the control, edgehold, and power from your tip and tail to under your feet where your balance in centered, resulting in a more catch free tip and tail. Better control for freestyle tricks, better tracking and an easier snowboard to ride. 
 
Sintered UHMW Base is so fast, you might be mistaken for T. Rice himself.

title: YAMAHA R6 00 TRACK RACE BIKE EXCELLENT WITH CA TITLE.
description:
Hi, 
 
Selling my track bike. It is a beautiful bike that needs nothing. OK, THIS IS A TRACK BIKE, WHAT DOES IT MEAN?? IT MEANS IT CAN NOT BE RIDDEN ON THE STREET AS IT IS. 
You could make it street legal, but it would take some work. 
All DMV fees are up to date and it is under my name with a California salvage title. The bike has a non- operable registration right now with all fees for 2016 paid off. 
This bike has never ever been raced or crashed, just taken 3/4 times to the track only. No beat up bike or abused engine /parts here. 
I just had the whole front suspension (front and back) rebuilt by catalyst reaction 3 weeks ago (I have paper work to prove it). 
It has a new chain and sprockets, clean title, all new fluids, safety wired, go pro mounts in three places, new spark plugs, new air filter (K&N) , newer EBC double H brake pads front and rear, new front and rear galfer steel brake lines, fresh mobil 1 motor oil, K&N oil filter, new Pro factory clutch cable, new throttle cables, rebuilt carb serviced by evolution cycles and catalyst reaction with upgraded pro factory jet kit and it is painted with the Valentino Rossi theme 
Why spending so much to sell it? Simple, I wasn't planning on selling it. 
I'm not a racer, just an enthusiast (group C, go figured). 
This bike has been set up for the track, making it street legal would be possible, but it will take work, sometimes the work is too much and for many people is not worth it. 
I don't need money or need to sell fast, so don't bother with offers. 
I put heart and soul (and a fair amount of money) into this bike. The price is not "sentimental value". The bikes needs nothing and it is well priced. 
It has a CA title(rare for track bikes) and it's CA registered 
If it doesn't sell in a few weeks, I'll keep her as a back up bike. Have several extra parts. 
CASH ONLY. NO TRADES. 
Please do not ask if is still available or if I want to trade it for whatever is that you have. I'm looking to downsize, otherwise I wouldn't sale it. 
Does it still available questions will be ignored. If the ad is up, the bike still available. 
Thank you for reading.

title: Black & White Alloy 56cm Track Bike w/ Carbon Fork
description:
Beautiful super light State Bicycle custom tack bike. 
Recently build from some spare/new parts. 
Good to go as is but perfect as a project with a mix of high quality and average parts. 
 
Killer parts: 
-- State Bicycle Black Label 6061 alloy frame (56cm - state bike runs small so more like a common 54cm) 
-- State Bicycle carbon fork 
-- SRAM S100 crankset 
-- Thompson alloy seat post 
-- Classic MKS NJS stamped pedals 
-- Super comfy long Forte TT seat 
-- Brand new chain! 
 
Good enough parts: 
-- Flipflop Wheelset - roll well and are strong but are a bit too heavy to be on an alloy/carbon bike 
-- State Bicycle stock brakes (have an extra one for the rear but it's a goofy color) 
-- State Bicycle stock drop bars 
-- State Bicycle stock stem 
-- Rocket 46T chainring 
 
All the qualities parts look amazing, however the previous owner of the wheel set, bars, and stem tried to paint them to match the frame. They don't look bad but the paint surely won't last as long as a pro job!
attributes: excellent State Bicycle Co. + Black Label 6061 56cm

title: Rossingol Soul V SKIS (178cm) + Fritsche Freeride AT/Alpine BINDINGS
description:
Used pair of Rossingol Soul V Ski's + Fritsche Freeride AT/Alpine Bindings (mounted). 
Still in very solid condition, not beat up; but not a new setup. 
 
This is uniquely a setup that is a both a backcountry and resort/alpine setup, because Fritsche Freeride's are touring bindings. 
But they can also be used as a resort setup because these are one of the few bindings that are compatible with Alpine Ski Boot sole blocks. 
Most 'backcountry' bindings will only pair with AT or tech specific boots. 
These will pair with either. 
 
SKIS 
Great pair if you're looking to get on a first backcountry setup for a nice price, want a park, carving or all-mountain ski, or just want a ready to go setup for a sierra rock ski. 
It's a all-wood core ski that is very responsive to turn, and adaptable to on and off piste skiing conditions. 
Ski's are Rossingol Soul V's. 
178cm length. 
Any base scratches have been p-tex repaired by myself. 
Ski is waxed and ready to go. 
 
BINDINGS 
Fritsche Freeride Bindings with a 12 DIN  and 108mm ski brake are professionally mounted and included. 
Bindings are in solid condition. 
Retail price of this binding alone is $500. 
A great touring binding, I'm happy to share my experience of how well they climb, downhill and all the rest. 
 
More details on the bindings: 
http://www.backcountry.com/black-diamond-fritschi-diamir-freeride-pro-binding-108mm 
 
Happy to talk more about the best conditions for this ski setup, getting started backcountry skiing or the finer points of the art, or just skis/bindings general. 
I'm letting this ski/bindings setup go as I've invested in a full new tech setup this season. 
 
Email me with your phone number if you're interested, and we'll schedule a time for you to check them out. 
Price is mostly firm. 
Thanks.

title: Proceed AVP S Preamp Processor  $475 obo
description:
I'm selling a used great condition Proceed AVP S Preamp Processor. This unit sounds and works great. Includes remote. 
 
Original MSRP $4995. Asking $475obo 
 
Please call or text if interested 
  
 
 
The Proceed AVP is a full function audio/video preamp that combines audio preamplification, digital conversion, broadcast-quality video switching and surround sound decoding into a highly refined high-end gem. Priced at $4,995 (S-Video version), the Proceed AVP comes equipped with DTS, AC3, Pro Logic, THX and numerous other surround fields for both music and video playback. The digital section of the AVP uses Burr Brown 1702 20-bit Multibit DACs for the left and right channels and 1-bit, 24-bit compatible AKM Delta-Sigma DACs for the center, surround, aux and subwoofer channels. A dealer-provided software update will be available in the near future to get your AVP ready for the 24-bit 96 kHz performance. 
 
The AVP comes equipped with seven digital and eight analog highly flexible, assignable inputs. A special version of the AVP can be ordered in order to take up to four S-VHS inputs, as well as four composite inputs. A standard AVP comes with six composite video inputs. During the set-up process, you decide which audio and or video device is to go into what input. For example, you can set the primary and secondary input method; a DVD player would take a digital input first and possibly an analog second. The set-up process is not a cakewalk, but it is logical and intuitive. The AVP manual is among the best I have ever read, in that it is complete and easy to understand for the end user. 
 
The faceplate of the Proceed AVP has a non-traditional design that incorporates a sexy modern look with useful buttons in unconventional placements. The controls for the loudspeaker level adjusters are curved around the beautifully milled volume knob. This makes lots of sense in that the volume knob has a dual purpose: it also controls the surround parameters when desired. 
 
The design for the Proceed AVP's remote is unique in that, unlike its competitors, it fits easily in your hand and features only nine buttons. Each button is within reach of your thumb for both left- and right-handers. The three main buttons toggle up and down smoothly. However, I frequently found myself making the mistake of switching my inputs when I wanted to lower the volume. Ultimately, I added a hand-held touch screen remote to control every component in my system, as well as to facilitate macros.   
 
Conclusion  
 
The Proceed AVP is the best value in all of the AV preamps. At $4995, it is far from cheap, but it has all of the features and high-end performance you'd expect from a Madrigal product; you would need to spend upwards of $15,000 to get anything comparable elsewhere. The fit and finish is great and the ease of use is much better than average. As a two-channel preamp, the Proceed AVP could replace nearly all of the existing preamps on the market even if you saved the surround features for future home theater upgrades. The Proceed AVP is a home run of a product. You'll be proud to own one as the centerpiece of your high performance multi-media system.

Its new..... Fly wild and fly sexy and safe.... Cheer.s. Happy New Year.. 
 
The Mavic from DJI packs features you once thought possible only on much larger platforms into a compact quadcopter that is snappy, agile, and captures high-resolution images. The drone features an advanced flight control system that draws on a host of sensors -- including a ground-facing camera, ultrasound, GPS, dual redundant IMUs, and more -- to keep track of where it is flying in 3D space and even avoid collisions. The Mavic works in tandem with DJI's GO mobile app for accessing settings, getting a telemetry readout, viewing a low-latency video feed, and even editing and sharing your footage. In addition traditional joystick style controls, you can fly with simple tap-based commands, and the Mavic can even recognize gestures for the perfect selfie. 
PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS 
 
Gimbal-Stabilized 12MP / 4K Camera 
OcuSync Transmission Technology 
Up to 4.3 Mile Control Range 
Up to 27 Minutes Flight Time 
GPS- & Vision Position-Based Navigation 
FlightAutonomy with Obstacle Detection 
DJI GO App-Based Control and Monitoring 
Top Speed of 40 mph in Sport Mode 
ActiveTrack Subject Tracking Modes

The Mavic from DJI packs features you once thought possible only on much larger platforms into a compact quadcopter that is snappy, agile, and captures high-resolution images. The drone features an advanced flight control system that draws on a host of sensors -- including a ground-facing camera, ultrasound, GPS, dual redundant IMUs, and more -- to keep track of where it is flying in 3D space and even avoid collisions. The Mavic works in tandem with DJI's GO mobile app for accessing settings, getting a telemetry readout, viewing a low-latency video feed, and even editing and sharing your footage. In addition traditional joystick style controls, you can fly with simple tap-based commands, and the Mavic can even recognize gestures for the perfect selfie.

OcuSync Transmission Technology 
Up to 4.3 Mile Control Range 
Up to 27 Minutes Flight Time 
GPS- & Vision Position-Based Navigation

DJI GO App-Based Control and Monitoring

title: fits 5'4"-5'8" 46cm 2015 Fuji Tread 1.0 Disc Road Cyclecross Bike
description:
I'm selling my nearly-new Fuji because my SO keeps building me custom bikes this go-anywhere bike is ready to find a new home. Forget what the bike shop guy told you your size is, this is a cyclecross bike and built  for someone between 5'4" and 5'9". I am 5'4 and I have really had to work to make my body fit the long geometry. Here are the details that make her worth every penny of $500 (listing price $1500), despite the admittedly lame way that the paint has chipped. 
 
1. Disc brakes. That means you can hitch on the trailer or baby bike seat and feel totally comfortable in all weather, any hill, no problem. They are perfectly tuned up, but if you want, I am happy to give you the free tune up card I have from Performance Bicycles.  
2. Basically brand new tires. These are cyclocross tires, which means that they are skinny enough to fly down the roads, but beefy enough that you can conquer Oakland or Mission Street (or trails, which is what they were meant for) and not feel like you are taking your life in your hands.  
3. This bike is waaaayyyy lighter than a touring bike but does the same job. Go camping, go off road, across the country, up the two flights of stairs to your place or on bart. The frame can handle it and picking it up is a breeze.  
4. Because of my size, I upgraded the handlebar stem to a Ritchie fully adjustable stem ($50). You can adjust to make the exact position that is right for you.  
5. Shimano clip-in combo petals. Wear your street shoes, wear your biking shoes, no problem and a great low profile. ($75) 
6. Topeak rear rack. Yes, this bike is so light-yet-beefy, you will want to haul things around. ($35) 
7. It isn't stolen! Your karma is safe and the bottom bracket numbers are fully intact.  
 
 
 
 
Straight from the horse's mouth:  
Built for the road less traveled, the Fuji Tread 1.0 disc road bike is perfectly at home on pavement, gravel, dirt, and everything in between. Exclusive to Performance, the Tread 1.0 mates a durable and lightweight aluminum frameset to premium components for a go-anywhere, do anything adventure machine. The Fuji A6-SL custom-butted alloy frame is light enough to ride on the road, but durable enough for the dirt, and features huge tire clearances so you can run whatever rubber you need to get the job done. A carbon fiber fork keeps things smooth and the gram count low. Shifting falls to Shimano's excellent redesigned 105 5800 11-speed components. Benefitting from a flood of trickle down technology from the pro-level Dura-Ace and Ultegra groups, 105 has gotten refined ergonomics, improved shifting performance, and an extra gear so you always have the right one. Tektro mechanical disc brakes give you plenty of braking power and control, on all kinds of terrain and in all-weather conditions. Big, wide 700x35 super premium X'Plore tires from Clement give you flat protection and a smooth, supple road feel that'll keep you rolling from rough city streets to some deep and chunky gravel.

Fender Princeton Reverb Reissue-Orange and White, with get this a West Coast Custom powered pedal board and matching suitcase for it!!! Custom Luggage for your stuff. You can carry everything you need in both hands. Amp / Suitcase / Guitar.  
 
The tone that comes out of these amps is simply delightful. No wonder this is the ultimate pro go to practice amp for the living room or studio. Has almost as many tubes as the my Mesa Dual Rectifier. 
 
It has only a couple of hours on it. It has been sitting in the closet for too long. Never left my house. Always covered. Still Brand New. 
 
The custom board and custom case for it cost almost as much as the amp. 
 
Made in USA 
Amp Type: Vintage Reissue Series Tube Amp 
Output: 15 watts into 8 ohms 
Tubes: 3 x 12AX7, 1 x 12AT7, 2 x Groove Tubes 6V6, 1 x 5AR4 rectifier tube 
Speaker: 1-10" Jensen Special Design C-10R 
Channel: 1 channel (2 inputs) 
Controls: Volume, Treble, Bass, Reverb, Speed, Intensity 
Effects: Reverb, Vibrato 
 
The Amps go for 999. I've got 700 into the custom Pedal Board and Matching Case. 
 
I'll take a reasonable offer. 
 
Lowballs take note. Your not only wasting my time. Your really wasting YOUR time.

title: 250 CC QUAD ATV LIKE NEW - Never Ridden-
description:
2015 250CC TAO Quad for sale.  
 
Originally bought this for my wife last year and she didn't like the clutch. Bought her an automatic instead and kept this one thinking I would use it myself for ranch work which never happened. The quad doesn't even have an hour on the motor. To top it off, I changed out the stock battery (because I believe they aren't that good) as well as the stock chain with a heavier duty one (for the same reason, stock chains aren't that great). After changing those things out we only used the other quad we had and the wife's new one. This one has simply sat, with brand new battery, brand new chain, brand new ties, brand new everything only to have the tank drained of old gas and fired up once a month to keep the motor new and turning.  
 
Also installed a battery tender (which is plugged in always) and will give it to the new owner. The 250 quads are over 2K brand new, and this one hasn't been taken off road or worked at all, super clean.  
 
This ATV also COMES REGISTERED OFF ROAD READY (STICKERS AND ALL) through June 2017! No need to hit the DMV and go through the off road registration BS you will need to buying from other sellers on Craigslist. Trust me, you do not want to be stopped by the county sheriff 's or Fish & Game with out having the CA off road legit stickers/registration, it is bad news! This QUAD is READY TO GO! -PINK IN HAND- 
 
Pro's: Everything is brand new (Look at the pics: no dirt on the tires, shocks, anything). Has headlights, tail light, brake lights, high beams, low beams, front rack and a back rack. Perfect for ranching or a bit of fun. Come start'er up and see for yourself!  
 
Con's: Small crack in the front plastic grill guard from the wife driving/loading it in to the pick up (hence why she doesn't want a clutch) which can be seen in the pic, low left facing the quad. 
 
$1,500 OBO - No reasonable offer will be refused CASH IS KING! Call or Text Matt: 
  
(I work from home and available most times/days)

title: Sony Cyber-shot DSC-H55 14.1MP Digital Camera with 10x Wide Angle Opti
description:
Sony Cyber-shot DSC-H55 14.1MP Digital Camera with 10x Wide Angle Optical Zoom with SteadyShot Image Stabilization and 3.0 inch LCD (Black)  
 
 
3.0-inch Clear Photo LCD display (230k pixels) 
 Compose and show off your images on the large 3.0-inch (230K) Clear Photo LCD display, which features a special anti-reflective coating for sharp visibility, even in bright sunlight.  
 
10x (25mm-equivalent) professional-quality optical zoom G-Lens 
 G lenses are used in top of the line digital single lens reflex (DSLR) cameras and advanced pro-sumer HD camcorders. Capture the action up close with the 10x optical zoom, and with the 25mm equivalent wide angle lens the H55 even allows you to capture more of the scenes in landscape or group portraits.  
 
14.1-megapixel Super HAD CCD image sensor 
 A powerful 14.1-megapixel, 1/2.3-inch Super HAD CCD image sensor helps you capture gorgeous images with superb contrast and clarity down to the finest detail. With 14.1 megapixels, you can create stunning, photo-quality prints up to A3+ (13 x 19") size, or crop your images and still come away with high resolution shots.  
 
Sweep Panorama mode 
 Reach beyond the traditional wide angle lens, and capture more breathtaking shots with Sweep Panorama Mode. Simply press the shutter button and sweep the camera horizontal or vertically and the camera continuously shoots at a high speed, then seamlessly stitches the images together with automatic position adjustment to create one stunning panoramic image. Available in wide and ultra-wide options, the camera can take panoramic shots of up to 243 degrees. Now capturing wide landscapes is as easy as press and sweep.  
 
 
720p HD MP4 Movie Mode 
 720p MP4 is a popular format for high definition video that compresses the size of your audio and video, making your media files small enough to easily transfer to your compatible PC or Mac. MP4 is also highly compatible with the Web, so you can effortlessly upload your media to popular photo or video-sharing Web sites like Photobucket or YouTube. (Compatible PC with internet capability required).  
 
BIONZ Image Processor 
 The BIONZ image processor delivers the high resolution and fast performance you expect from a Sony digital camera. Fast processing enables unique Sony features such as Sweep Panorama, Handheld Twilight, Antimotion Blur, HDR, etc to take and combine multiple images in less than a second to create wide panoramic images. Images have reduced grain and appear less washed out.  
 
 
Self-Portrait Timer 
 Self-Portrait Timer helps take the guesswork out of self portraits by utilizing Face Detection technology to recognize when your face enters the frame. Once the camera detects your face, it triggers a 2-second timer, and then snaps a picture.  
 
Intelligent Auto (iAuto) mode 
 Unlike traditional auto mode, Intelligent Auto (iAuto) mode thinks for you, recognizing scenes, lighting conditions, and faces, and adjusts settings resulting in clearer images, faces with more natural skin tone, and less blur. By incorporating advanced features such as Intelligent Scene Recognition, Face Detection technology, and Optical SteadyShot image stabilization, iAuto mode lets you take advantage of the latest Sony Cyber-shot technology without leaving auto mode. Whether you're shooting landscapes, capturing a beautiful flower, or taking pictures at an in-door birthday party or wedding shower, iAuto mode will optimize your camera's settings to help ensure you come away with a great shot.  
 
Intelligent Scene Recognition (iSCN) Mode 
 Intelligent Scene Recognition (iSCN) Mode automatically detects eight different types of scenes and, within just 1/30th of a second, selects the appropriate camera settings: Backlight, Backlight Portrait, Twilight, Twilight Portrait, Twilight using a tripod, Portrait, Landscape, and Macro. iSCN has two modes: Auto and Advanced. In Auto Mode, the camera takes a single shot using the optimal settings. In Advanced Mode, the camera takes a photo with the optimal settings and, if in difficult lighting (low light or back light) immediately takes a second photo with another optimized setting so you can choose which to keep.  
 
Optical SteadyShot image stabilization 
 Optical SteadyShot image stabilization uses a built-in gyro sensor to detect camera shake and automatically compensates to help prevent blur without sacrificing image quality.  
 
Optical SteadyShot image stabilization w/ Active Mode 
 Optical SteadyShot image stabilization with Active Mode gives you the freedom to shoot movies even while walking or running. By providing up to 10x the correction of standard mode, Active Mode can compensate for excessive camera shake so you can move along with your subject while shooting.  
 
High Sensitivity Mode (ISO 3200) 
 High ISO allows for faster shutter speed, so you can take photos indoors or in low light without the need for a flash. In addition to High Sensitivity Mode (ISO), you can select up to seven ISO settings (Auto, 80, 100, 200, 
  
 3200) when shooting in Program Auto Mode to adjust sensitivity to your shooting conditions.  
 
Face Detection technology 
Sony's Face Detection technology can automatically distinguish between children and adults. Face Detection technology detects up to eight individual faces and adjusts flash, focus, exposure, and white balance to help deliver crisp, properly lit images of family and friends.  
 
Motion Detection 
 Motion Detection, along with Face Motion Detection adjusts ISO sensitivity and increases the shutter speed when movement is detected, reducing blur in moving subjects and faces.  
 
Anti-blink Function 
 It's frustrating to think you've captured that perfect shot, only to review it later and discover one of your subjects blinked just as you pressed the shutter. When the camera is set to Soft Snap, the Anti-blink function captures two images, recording only the photo with less squinting or blinking. If a blink is detected in other shooting modes, a warning will be displayed after you take the shot.  
 
Smile Shutter technology 
 Smile Shutter technology captures a smile the moment it happens. Simply press the Smile Shutter button and the camera does the rest. You can also select adult and child priority and indicate the degree of Smile Detection Sensitivity. Intelligent Scene Recognition can be used together with Smile Shutter mode. This means that beautiful smiles can be captured with settings optimized for the particular scene, even in difficult conditions such as twilight and backlighting.  
 
Dynamic Range Optimizer Standard and Plus 
 Dynamic Range Optimizer (DRO) Standard and Plus uses a sophisticated algorithm to help recover shadows and highlights. The result is more natural images with clearer details that more closely match what your naked eye sees. DRO is particularly effective when shooting backlit portraits or any scene with a dramatic contrast between background and foreground lighting. DRO Plus allows for even greater optimization by analyzing each region of an image and performing additional image processing.  
 
Intelligent AF 
 Thanks to Intelligent AF technology, capture fleeting moments like a child's adorable expression with the ultra-quick AF which locks focus in as little as 0.3-sec.  
 
Scene modes 
 The DSC-H55 features 11 convenient scene modes: High Sensitivity, Twilight, Twilight Portrait, Soft Snap, Landscape, Beach, Snow, Fireworks, Advanced Sports, Gourmet, Pet.  
 
Easy Shooting Mode 
 With Easy Shooting Mode, even beginners can take great photos. In Easy Shooting Mode, easy-to-understand basic instructions are displayed on the LCD screen and the camera switches to all automatic settings, removing several function choices and allowing you to focus on just your subject. Since this mode works together with Intelligent Scene Recognition, the camera selects the optimum setting for each scene. In addition the easy mode simplifies preview mode.  
 
Function Guide 
 This beginner-friendly optional function helps navigate through the various functions and settings displaying the description of chosen functions or settings on the LCD screen.  
 
PHOTOMUSIC 
 PHOTOMUSIC combines images with music (4 tracks, 5 minutes per track) to produce fun and entertaining slide shows with standard visual effects (Simple, Nostalgic, Active, and Stylish). Select from pre-loaded tracks on the camera or transfer your own from your compatible computer (sold separately).  
 
Viewing modes 
 Find your photos using the simple folder or calendar viewing modes.  
 
In-Camera retouching tools 
 Retouch and enhance your photos on the go with in-camera Trimming, Red-Eye Correction, and Unsharp Masking functions.  
 
 
PhotoTV HD 
 Bring your photos to life and enjoy highly detailed, high definition images with PhotoTV HD-capable Sony BRAVIA HDTVs. PhotoTV HD fine tunes settings on your PhotoTV HD enabled BRAVIA HDTV, such as sharpness, gradation, and color to display images that look more like printed photos.  
 
Lithium-ion battery 
 Included lithium-ion battery provides added convenience with longer lasting power than alkaline batteries (capacity of supplied battery is 310 images or 155 minutes for shooting still images). Additional battery available for purchase add more power and information  
 
Media card slot  
For convenient storage and sharing of your images, the DSC-H55 accepts Memory Stick Duo/Memory Stick PRO Duo/Memory Stick PRO-HG Duo media (sold separately) or SD/SDHC media (sold separately).  
 
SD Card Functionality 
 Sony SD memory cards are the perfect solution for storing and sharing your digital content such as high-quality photos, videos, music, and more.  
 
Includes : original battery, 2 brand new after market batteries, after market travel(car&wall) charger

title: 1 JBL LE14H-1 Woofer Fresh Foam: 250Ti L250 240Ti Citation 7.4 PS1400
description:
Very Good Condition & Refurbished with Fresh Foam Surround - Ready to Go! 
 
One JBL LE14H-1 Woofer for L250, 250Ti, 240Ti, Citation 7.4 Subwoofer or Fosgate Audionics FS400 Subwoofer 
 
Fits JBL Synthesis PS1400 Sub Too! 
 
This black Aquaplas cone woofer used primarily in the L250, 250Ti and 240Ti systems. 
 
Also JBL / Harman Kardon Citation THX 7.4 Subwoofer or the Fosgate Audionics FS400 Subwoofer plus fits in the JBL Synthesis PS1400 Subwoofer too! 
 
Maybe others. . ..? 
 
Low Frequency Transducer: Model LE14H-1 
14" Woofer: 114dB / 300 watts / Nominal Impedance 8 ohm 
Positive Red = Negative Pressure / Inward 
Felted paper cone laminated with Aquaplas, cast aluminum frame, nominal 14 inch diameter, 4 inch copper voice coil, 19 lbs. magnet and refurbished with new foam surround plus a 24-hour Burn-In. 
 
Refurbished by VSN  
Removed Rotten Foam: Surround / Internal Disk 
Cleaned: Basket & Cone 
Inspected: Input Terminals / Spider 
Installed New: Foam Surround / Port Mesh Screen 
Confirmed with Sound: Clear and Smooth 
 
The surround is brand new and tested all the way to Xmax with a 30Hz signal to verify the voice coil do not rub. 
 
And look......Pro Input Terminals and fits 12awg wire, not the early consumer version inputs! 
 
In addition to getting a new foam surround, the internal foam disk used as a screen over the magnet port has been removed and replaced with a non-rotting fine mesh screen on the exterior and under the foilcal.  Note: The original back label was missing, this foilcal is a spare in my shop. 
 
Sadly this OEM foam disk ends up rotting away just like the surround does and in the worst case scenario the gooey mess ends up binding the voice coil at the pole piece. 
 
This has become a standard replacement on all JBL drivers I service as a preventive measure after removing too many cones to clean up the voice coil and gap!

title: Refurbished JBL 127H-1 Woofers w/ Fresh Foam: L80T  4410  XPL160

description:

One Pair of JBL LE14H-1 Woofers with Fresh Foam Surrounds - Ready to Go! 
 
This black Aquaplas cone woofer used primarily in the L250, 250Ti and 240Ti systems. 
 
Also JBL / Harman Kardon Citation THX 7.4 Subwoofer or the Fosgate Audionics FS400 Subwoofer plus fits in the JBL Synthesis PS1400 Subwoofer too! 
 
Low Frequency Transducer: Model LE14H-1 
14" Woofer: 114dB / 300 watts / Nominal Impedance 8 ohm 
Positive Red = Negative Pressure / Inward 
Felted paper cone laminated with Aquaplas, cast aluminum frame, nominal 14 inch diameter, 4 inch copper voice coil, 19 lbs. magnet and refurbished with new foam surrounds plus a 24-hour Burn-In. 
 
Refurbished by VSN on eBay 
Removed Rotten Foam: Surrounds / Internal Disks 
Cleaned: Baskets & Cones 
Inspected: Input Terminals / Spiders 
Minor Repair: One Aftermarket Dust Cap on the "Right" 
Installed New: Foam Surrounds / Port Mesh Screens 
Confirmed with Sound: Clear and Smooth 
 
The surrounds are brand new and tested all the way to Xmax with a 30Hz signal to verify the voice coils do not rub. 
 
And look......Pro Input Terminals and fits 12awg wire, not the early consumer version inputs! 
 
In addition to getting a new foam surround, the internal foam disk used as a screen over the magnet port has been removed and replaced with a non-rotting fine mesh screen on the exterior and under the foilcal. 
 
Sadly this OEM foam disk ends up rotting away just like the surround does and in the worst case scenario the gooey mess ends up binding the voice coil at the pole piece. 
 
This has become a standard replacement on all JBL drivers I service as a preventive measure after removing too many cones to clean up the voice coil and gap! 
 
I'm a retired manufacturing engineer with a passion to repair & refurbish drivers, plus modify & enhance vintage stereo speakers with a primary focus on JBL. 
 
My service rate for restore your LE14H-1 drivers with new foam surrounds is $150 a pair 
IF you tried to install new foam first, my rate is double!

title: BOB Yak tow-behind bike trailer for bike touring
description:
Thinking about bike touring? This is an amazing gear choice. Mix it with a Northface Basecamp Duffel and you have a complete gear set. The trailer is not the lightest option, and can make those hills a little bit tougher to get up. I'm a strong cyclist, and as a result it worked great for me. The downhill will be unlike anything else available though. It tracks behind the bike way smoother than the pannier option.  
 
Con - heavier than panniers (not a lot though once you get done with front and rear racks) 
Pro - One bag (some people like having 5 little bags) that can hold larger items easy. No longer strapping tent poles to the top tub that chafes while you ride... 
Pro - Downhill bliss - I hit 55 mph with this thing (not the smartest idea btw, but amazing. That gives you an idea how great the ride is) 
Con - not easy to put on a plane - doable though 
 
Why am I selling it? First kid on the way, storing this just doesn't make sense for us. Being a gear-junky, letting this piece go is a bit tough. Hope someone else can enjoy it.  
 
From the manufacturer: 
Our first BOB trailer set the standard for all others to come: tough, dependable and ready to roll wherever life moves you. The Yak Trailer carries up to 70 pounds of what you need to ride longer and further. It attaches to most bicycles' rear wheel hub, creating a low and stable center of gravity with excellent aerodynamics.   
http://www.bobgear.com/bike-trailers/yak
