title: Line 6 Sonic Port
description:
48 kHz · 24-bit 
Get legendary Line 6 amp and effect models on your iOS device with pristine, pro-quality audio. Sonic Port provides an incredible 110dB of dynamic range on the guitar input, to capture your full range of expression and works with GarageBand, the free Mobile POD app, and much more.  
 
You can even use it to play live.Jam with the Tone of Your Favorite Artists. World-famous guitarists depend on Line 6 POD multi-effects for amazing tone in the studio and on stage. The free Mobile POD app brings these legendary tones to your iOS device. Mobile POD includes over 10,000 presets designed by artists, Line 6 and other players, so you can call up the right tone in an instant. 
 
If you want to go further, you can mix and match 32 amps, 16 stompbox and rack effects, and 16 speaker cabinets for an impressive array of sounds. The intuitive interface makes it easy to tweak and save your custom tones. Mobile POD also lets you play along with your iTunes library* using your custom tones. 
 
Learn, Jam and Record with Hit Songs. Sonic Port works with the award-winning Jammit app-the first to let you play along with real, multi-track master recordings from major artists. Jammit isolates individual audio tracks within original master recordings, so you can learn, jam and record along with your favorite songs as played by the original artists. 
 
You can isolate your instrument from the track for closer scrutiny, loop the track for extended practice or slow it down to a comfortable pace for learning. With Sonic Port as the guitar interface, Jammit loads perfectly matched Line 6 tones for a variety of its jam tracks, automatically changing the sound when needed as the song plays.Plug into iOS Creativity Sonic Port makes it easy to connect your guitar or bass to your iOS device and start making music. Simply plug your instrument into the 1/4" guitar input, launch GarageBand. 
 
The centerpiece of your GarageBand mobile studio Get the authentic tones of your favorite artistsor create your own The only system that lets you jam along with original hit recordings (with the free Jammit app)Includes detachable Lightning and 30-pin cables Completely powered by iOS device

title: 2016 Lynskey R240 Titanium Disc Road Bike
description:
Hey folks, 
 
I'm regretfully selling my 2016 Lynskey Titanium R240 disc road bike (in size small) with the latest Shimano Ultegra hydraulic disc brakes that I built up earlier this year but have not had time to ride.  This was my dream bike build and I spent copious amounts of money, time researching and building up the bike.  It has the latest road bike tech included ( disc brakes, tapered head tube, tapered carbon steerer/fork, 135mm rear spacing, etc).  You can also convert this bike to the latest thru-axle technology to really stiffen up the ride,  basically this frame is future proofed (atleast for now).  I'm 5'6" and this bike should comfortably fit someone between 5'3"-5'9" depending on your proportions. 
 
The bike only has approx. 100 miles on it and everything is in excellent condition.  This bike rides soooo smooth, fast, nimble and the power goes straight to the wheels.  I've ridden carbon road bikes in the past and titanium really is the way to go as it's stiff and takes out all of the harshness/noises (carbon creaks) in the ride that carbon has.  The hydraulic disc brake stopping power is insanely better than mechanical discs or rim brakes.  Titanium frames will last a lifetime, if you crash/drop/knick/ding/breathe on your bike, you don't have to worry about cracks like carbon bikes. 
 
Here's the specs: 
 
Frame:  2016 Lynskey R240 Disc titanium frame 
Fork:  Lynskey Pro Carbon #3 disc fork/Cane Creek 40 1.5" tapered headset 
Headset:  Cane Creek 40 1.5" tapered headset 
Front Derailleur:  Shimano Ultegra 6800 34.9 clamp-on front derailluer 
Rear Derailleur:  Shimano RD-6800, Ultegra GS 11-spd 
Crankset:  Shimano Ultegra 6700 Compact 50/34T crankset (this is the only slightly used part of the entire build, has 400 miles on the crank) 
Cassette/Freewheel:  Shimano CS-6800, Ultegra, 11-spd, 11-32T 
Bottom Bracket:  Shimano BBR60 Ultegra Bottom Bracket 
Shifters:  Shimano shifter/brake levers, ST-RS685 2x11 Speed 
Chain:  Shimano CN-HG700-11, FOR 11-spd (road/mtn) 
Brakes Calipers:  Shimano Disc-brake BR-RS785 
Brake Levers:  Shimano integrated ST-RS685 Hydraulic 
Brake Rotors:  Shimano SM-RT76 XT 160MM, 6-bolt 
Handlebar:  Giant Contact, 31.8 (40cm) 
Stem:  Easton ea90 100mm 
Seat Post:  Specialized 25mm offset 27.2 x 400mm Seatpost 
Rims:  Vuelta Corsa Lite DR Disc Road Wheelset (tubeless compatible) 
Tires:  Contintental Grand sport race 700x25c tires 
 
The bike will not come with a saddle or pedals as these are rider specific but i'll have pedals/saddle installed for the test ride.  i'd like for it to go to a good home where it'll be ridden, idolized and appreciated! 
 
 
I'm asking $3200 cash firm, it cost me alot more to build (the frame alone is $2100!).  Please only email me if you're seriously interested and willing to pay my asking price in cash.  Collateral (Car keys, wallet or credit card) will be required before any test rides will be granted.  We'll meet in a public, well-lit location that's safe for both parties.   
 
NO LOWBALLERS, SCAMMERS OR TIREKICKERS!!!  IF THE AD IS STILL UP THEN THE BIKE IS STILL FOR SALE.  NO PARTING OUT.  Thank you for looking and ride safe!

title: 2016 Gibson Les Paul Traditional with upgrades
description:
Beautiful 2016 Gibson Les Paul Traditional in honey burst with flamed maple plus top.  This is the Traditional Plus model that is the same as the Gibson Les Paul Standard up until they started chambering the Standard in 2007, it is NOT the cheaper version "Traditional Pro" made for Guitar Center without a nitro finish, chambered, lower grade maple tops, etc.   
 
The electronics have been upgraded with a RS Guitar Works vintage 50s wiring kit and DiMarzio 36th Anniversary PAF-style pickups.  Incredible, classic tone and responsiveness from the controls! 
 
Weighs less than 9.1 pounds on the post office scale.  
 
I bought this as a backup for my 1959 Historic Reissue but can't justify having both guitars, so I've put both up for sale and will keep the one that doesn't sell. In order for it to look more like a 1959 burst, the speed knobs were replaced with amber tophats, "poker chip" and switch tip swapped for more vintage colored plastic, and the "Traditional" truss rod cover replaced with a blank one.  The original hardware is still in the case.    
 
Tremendous feel and tone, the guitar is well set-up and ready to go!  There are some minor scratches from a belt buckle on the back that were hard to photograph, and two dings on the rear of the headstock  that are not visible from the front and don't affect the guitar in any way other than cosmetically.  I don't know how the dings happened, as they were there when I bought the guitar.   
 
Email, call, or text Eric at nine 7 0 - two three 7 - 9 8 two two.  Thanks!

title: Landscaping irrigation remote control
description:
For sale Hunter remote control commercial and residential 
$150.00 
Paypal: 
Shipping: 
Hunter Irrigation Sprinkler Commercial Remote Control Kit, New, ICR-Kit  
 
New, in very good working condition. Kit is complete except for the 4 AA batteries. It was bought some time ago, but never used. Batteries were removed due to age.  
 
For shopping centers, industrial complexes, college campuses, condominiums, and other expansive sites. If a remote control is going to work it needs the power to cover long-range distances. The ICR has a signal strong enough to go through obstructions such as buildings, walls, or trees and communicate with a controller for a half mile or more. When nothing is in its path, the ICR can function up to two miles from the controller. The ICR is a single unit that can be carried from job to job and used to remotely access dozens of diﬀerent irrigation systems (including any Hunter controller that operates with a SmartPort system). That eliminates going back and forth to the controller to start or stop a cycle during maintenance or installation. The task of winterizing a system becomes a one-person job instead of two.  
 
Features:  
· Over ½ mile typical range. Control sprinklers, valves, and pumps without going directly to the controller.  
· Compatible with all Hunter controllers. Designed to work with all Hunter ICC, Pro-C and SRC controllers through a SmartPort connection.  
· Large LCD display, push button operation. User-friendly features make the remote simple to use.  
· Variable remote activated station run times. Allows a one-time change in station run time duration without affecting the regular program.  
· Operates on 4 AA batteries for up to a year. Automatic shutoff extends battery life when not in use.  
· 128 different programmable security codes. Allows multiple ICR receivers to be used in the same area.  
· Rugged plastic carrying case. Foam lined case protects ICR from rough handling.  
 
Model ICR-KIT -- Complete Kit: transmitter, receiver, and wiring harness, 4 AA alkaline batteries (not included), and plastic carrying case  
· ICR-TR -- Hand held transmitter  
· ICR-R -- Receiver unit  
· ICR-Case - storage case  
· Smartport port adapter and wiring harness  
· 28 page Owner's User/Installation Manual (English, Spanish)  
 
Dimensions  
• Transmitter (w/o antenna): 6½" H x 3¼" W x 1¼" D (16.5 cm H x 8.3 cm W x 3.2 cm D)  
• Receiver (w/o antenna): 6¼" H x 3" W x 1¼" D (15.9 cm H x 7.6 cm W x 3.2 cm D)  
 
Speciﬁcations and Features  
• Address range: 0 to 127  
• Maximum stations supported: 48  
• Run times: Eight settings from 1-30 minutes  
• Range: Up to ½ mile obstructed, up to 2 mile line of sight  
• Temperature: 0-150˚ F  
• Humidity: Up to 100%  
• Transmitter: 4 AA alkaline batteries (not included)  
• Receiver: 24VAC, 0.05 Amps from controller through a SmartPort connector  
• System operating frequency: 27 MHz band  
• Install SmartPort up to 50' from controller (use SRR-SCWH shielded cable wiring harness)  
• No FCC license required  
• Rugged plastic carrying case included

description:

Hunter Irrigation Sprinkler Commercial Remote Control Kit, New, ICR-Kit  
 
New, in very good working condition. Kit is complete except for the 4 AA batteries. It was bought some time ago, but never used. Batteries were removed due to age.  
 
For shopping centers, industrial complexes, college campuses, condominiums, and other expansive sites. If a remote control is going to work it needs the power to cover long-range distances. The ICR has a signal strong enough to go through obstructions such as buildings, walls, or trees and communicate with a controller for a half mile or more. When nothing is in its path, the ICR can function up to two miles from the controller. The ICR is a single unit that can be carried from job to job and used to remotely access dozens of diﬀerent irrigation systems (including any Hunter controller that operates with a SmartPort system). That eliminates going back and forth to the controller to start or stop a cycle during maintenance or installation. The task of winterizing a system becomes a one-person job instead of two.

· Compatible with all Hunter controllers. Designed to work with all Hunter ICC, Pro-C and SRC controllers through a SmartPort connection.  
· Large LCD display, push button operation. User-friendly features make the remote simple to use.  
· Variable remote activated station run times. Allows a one-time change in station run time duration without affecting the regular program.  
· Operates on 4 AA batteries for up to a year. Automatic shutoff extends battery life when not in use.  
· 128 different programmable security codes. Allows multiple ICR receivers to be used in the same area.  
· Rugged plastic carrying case. Foam lined case protects ICR from rough handling.

title: Ceramic Beer Stoppers/Bottle Caps: Pre-pro - 100 years old (and signs)
description:
These Ceramic Beer Stoppers were dug by beer bottle diggers / archaeologists in the SF Bay Area. While the bottles sought are sometimes broken, these stoppers remain. Each has a beer logo on it from a defunct pre-prohibition brewery.  With the invention of the metal bottle cap, these stoppers became obsolete and scarce. Prohibition started in 1919. These are all from before this, possibly from the late 1800's. They are at least 96 years old, possibly 115 years old. They are in good condition for their age. The price is $10 each - your choice. The actual breweries on the stoppers may be different from the pictures as they sell. 
 
I have a significant collection of beer collectibles such as lighted /metal / plastic / cardboard signs, mirrors, tap handles / knobs, glass/ glasses, steins, mugs, beer cans, coasters, posters, labels, bottles, bottle caps, trays, match book covers, labels, openers, etc. Budweiser / Bud Light / Lite, Miller, Coors, Hamms, Sierra Nevada, Schlitz, St. Pauli Girl, Olympia, Pabst Blue Ribbon (PBR), Heineken, etc. - both domestic (USA) and foreign: German / Germany, England / Great Britain / United Kingdom (UK) / Scotland / Ireland, Japan, China, Russia, Italy, etc.  
 
If it advertised beer, I probably have it.  
 
Let me know if you're looking for something. Give me a call to arrange to see what I have. There is too much to send additional pictures beyond what is included here. Prices vary depending on the item, but start at $1.00 and go up from there. 
 
I have also other antiques / collectibles including Salvador Dali, Charles Schultz, bobbleheads, postcards, Mad Magazine paperback books, Coca Cola / Coke bottles/cans/signs/glasses, World War 2 / II, posters, glass telephone pole insulators, sports commemorative Wheaties boxes, radios, patches, fruit crate labels, etc. 
 
I also have vintage baseball, basketball and football cards from the 1950's to the present and other sports memorabilia available as well. Oakland Athletics / A's, San Francisco 49'ers / Niners, Oakland Raiders, Golden State Warriors, Sacramento Kings, San Jose Sharks, New York Yankees / Mets, Detroit Tigers, Atlanta Braves, Pittsburgh Pirates, Chicago Cubs / Bulls / Blackhawks, Los Angeles Lakers / Clippers / Dodgers / Angels / Kings, St. Louis Cardinals, Dallas Cowboys, Green Bay Packers, etc. I also have Oakland A's game used jersies and a Mark McGwire jersey. 
 
 Dave:

title: Gibson USA Les Paul Traditional Pro II  Fralin pickups
description:
Honey burst finish is beautiful!  excellent cosmetically, one small body ding only and a very slight residue from a decal that was on the body (photos do not capture)  Amazing tone with boutique Fralin humbucker pickups!  this LP stays in tune better than any I have ever had, and I have had close to 10 over the years.  I have moved to single coil guitars, so this must go!  Come check it out, it will be going on ebay soon.  50s neck is very comfortable, not too big, but no hand cramps like smaller necks..   2013 model year.  
 
http://www.guitarcenter.com/Gibson/Les-Paul-Traditional-Pro-II-50s-Neck-Electric-Guitar.gc 
 
Taking design and visual cues from the Les Pauls of the '80s and '90s, the Les Paul Traditional Pro II features powerful pickups with push/push for coil splits and boost circuit, '50s neck profile, Grover locking tuners, antique binding, period-correct pickguard, vintage Gibson top hat knobs, and the revolutionary Plek set up. 
 
With all the fat, sweet, snarling Les Paul tone that purists love, the new Gibson Les Paul Standard Traditional Pro II sports a mahogany body with a thick maple cap for the perfect blend of warmth and clarity. The top is finished in high-gloss lacquer, while the back, sides, and neck have a smooth satin finish that feels great and lets the wood resonate fully. Each Les Paul Traditional also comes with Gibson USA's standard black snakeskin case. 
 
no Period-Correct Pickguard 
 
 
stock Pickups: Neck - '57 Classic; Bridge - Super '57 
Among the qualities that make Gibson's original "Patent Applied For" humbucking pickups so unique are the subtle variations between coil windings. For the first few years of their productions‚Äî1955 to 1961‚ÄîGibson's PAF humbuckers were wound using imprecise machines, resulting in pickups with slightly different output and tone. The '57 Classic and Super '57 pickups are the result of Gibson's drive to capture and recreate this characteristic. Introduced in 1992, the '57 Classic at the neck provides warm, full tone with a balanced response, packing that classic Gibson PAF humbucker crunch, inspired by those original PAFs that received a few extra turns of wire. The Super '57 bridge pickup debuts in the Trad Pro with a wider frequency response and increased output. 
 
Both are made by Gibson to the exact same specs as the original PAFs, including Alnico II magnets, nickel-plated pole pieces, nickel slugs, maple spacers, and vintage-style, 2-conductor braided wiring. Gibson added poly-coated wiring, which improves consistency by eliminating thick or thin spots on the wiring, and wax potting, which removes all internal air space and any chance of microphonic feedback. 
 
Both pickups offer coil splitting for single-coil sounds and a boost circuit via push/push switching in the volume controls. ‚ÄúStraight Split‚Äù coil-splitting offers pure single coil tone and differs from LP Standards and Studios that have a ‚ÄúSuper Tap‚Äù coil-tap, which still has a small amount of humbucking. The boost circuit has a user-adjustable 10-dB boost for added power and frequency range for solos, single-note picking and dirty chording (depending on amp settings) and features true bypass that disengages the boost completely, ensuring pure passive Les Paul tone. 
 
Revolutionary Plek Set Up 
The Les Paul Traditional is the first model from Gibson USA to utilize the revolutionary Plek machine in setting up the guitar. The Plek is a German-made, computer-controlled machine that carefully measures each fret, along with the fingerboard height under each string, and then automatically dresses each fret, virtually eliminating string buzz and greatly improving the overall playability of the guitar. This pioneering process does in minutes what it takes a luthier several hours‚Äîsometimes even days‚Äîto accomplish. Every fret is accurately aligned, and the guitar is properly intonated, leaving the instrument "Plek'd" and amazingly playable. 
 
Antique Binding 
To see the process of putting the binding on the Les Paul Traditional is to really appreciate the effort and attention that Gibson puts into each instrument. A lone craftsman will carefully glue and fit 2 pieces of binding around the entire body of a Les Paul. He then winds a single, very long piece of narrow cloth around the entire body until the entire surface is nearly covered. The body is then hung to dry for a full 24 hours before it is unwrapped and moved into the next phase of production. It has been done the same way for over 100 years. Some question the value of adding binding, but Gibson believes it is a fundamental part of our rich guitar-making history. The binding adds elegance to the Les Paul Standard, and helps protect the edges of the body. The neck binding is installed over the fret ends, which eliminates sharp fret edges and provides for a smooth neck and easier playability.

I have installed a new 1,000 GB (1 TB) Samsung hard drive, maxed the ram out to 16 GB, removed the DVD drive to install a secondary 256 GB SSD and to top it all off the two hard drives are recognized as a single "Fusion" drive by the computer. This means the computer itself will automatically manage what files go on which hard drive so that the operating system, programs and files you use the most are available in an instant and load up to 10 times faster than a traditional hard drive! The battery is also brand new with only about 4 cycles on it, and since they're designed to last for at least 1,000 cycles you'll find years of use without issue! Everything is working perfectly including all ports and peripherals like camera, microphone, bluetooth and keyboard.
